TextBody: Dear Regina, My apologies. I was on leave previous week and this complaint was overlooked by my colleagues. I have registered this complaint in our system with ref. 28033. This product was produced in our facility in Tilburg (The Netherlands) on 6/06/23 and packed 7/06/23. First of all we apologies for this complaint.bBased on the picture we identify this as a piece of leafage. This product was produced the 7th of June 2023. No remarks were made during the production. Leafage is normally removed with the following equipment or processes: 1)Washing –inline process 2)‘Stalk removal fingers’- inline process –this is a device similar to a rake which catches any stalk passing on the production line. 3)Optical sorters- these are designed to identify any foreign bodies, such as leafage. It is very rare to get a complaint of this nature, but a piece of leafage must have passed through the system. Our Technical Team have checked the process sheets on the day, and all equipment appears to have been working correctly, with no notification of breakdowns or issues. We consider this as an isolated case. I have completed the document you have sent me. Please find in attachment. Please do not hesitate to contact me, if you have more questions. Kr, Michelle Michelle Bevernage Technical Sales Officer P +32 496 38 91 92 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Chan, Regina [regina.chan@simplot.com] Sent: 20/05/2024 06:55 To: Michelle.Bevernage@agristo.com Cc: Phillip.Dwyer@simplot.com Subject: Complaint 00654411 - Foreign object Hi Michelle, Hope you are well. Consumer has reported a foreign object in the potato, which she believes is mouse’s tail, see complaint attached. Can you please investigate and respond with findings and corrective actions by 27/05/24, thanks. TextBody: Hi Rachel, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. I have promptly registered it in our system under case number 28055. I am sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : B02 24 099 12:32 Production day : 07/04/2024 As you know, all incoming potatoes are inspected for quality (including length). During the potato intake, the potatoes are graded. Also during the production process itself, the potatoes go over a grading plate. This is a metal plate with holes in it - depending on the lenght of the chips, they can travel over the plate, or fall through the holes in the plate (and are rejected). When the product comes out of the freezer and right before it is packed, it goes over a second grading plate. This allows us to meet the specifications which are set on lenght. In addition, every hour the packed product is sampled and tested for quality, including length and slivers. QC documents of these records are retained. Based on the batch code, I have conducted a thorough investigation into the quality documents for this specific batch. I see that at the time the product in question was packed, we were indeed very close to the maximum tolerance on short pieces (< 25 mm). This may indeed explain the feeling of your customer. I understand this is the third claim we have in a short period on the same product, but it has to be noted that this is another type of claim (lenght) than the two others we have recently received (product clumps). Nevertheless, viewing our excellent relationship, we are willing to compensate the 8 boxes of your customer. I have launched a credit note request in our system. It's important to note that there will always be variations in production throughout the year due to the inherent nature of potatoes as a natural product. From a technical standpoint, we always strive to offer you the best possible product. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered, but hope to have solved this complaint to your satisfaction. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact me again.
Subject: FW: WP

First of all we apologies for this complaint.bBased on the picture we identify this as a piece of leafage. This product was produced the 7th of June 2023. No remarks were made during the production. Leafage is normally removed with the following equipment or processes: 1)Washing –inline process 2)‘Stalk removal fingers’- inline process –this is a device similar to a rake which catches any stalk passing on the production line. 3)Optical sorters- these are designed to identify any foreign bodies, such as leafage. It is very rare to get a complaint of this nature, but a piece of leafage must have passed through the system. Our Technical Team have checked the process sheets on the day, and all equipment appears to have been working correctly, with no notification of breakdowns or issues. We consider this as an isolated case. I have completed the document you have sent me. Please find in attachment. Please do not hesitate to contact me, if you have more questions. TextBody: Hello Ricardo Thank you for informing us about the issue reported here below. We have well received your complaint and have registered it in our system as reference 28103. Based on the lotcode, we traced back the production day to the 3rd of April 2024. We are sorry to hear that El Jefe was not satisfied with the quality of this product. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. The description of his complaint refers to the presence of black spots and bruises on the Corte Fino. As you know, all incoming potatoes are inspected for quality and defects. Afterwards, the potatoes pass an optical sorter. A second very sophisticated optical sorter is in place after the potatoes are cut, which also removes black spots from the potato pieces. In addition, every hour the packaged product is sampled and tested for quality, including blemishes, peel, green. QC documents of these records are retained. I have checked the production and tasting records of the concerned production batch and no remarks about sprout on potatoes have been noted. We produced well within the predefined specifications during the whole production batch for all parameters, including defects. [cid:image001.png@01DAB1A6.90496EB0] It's important to note that there will always be variations in production throughout the year due to the inherent nature of potatoes as a natural product. Especially at the end of the season, when potatoes have been stored for a longer period of time, the risk for bruises and thus black and brown spots becomes bigger. From a technical standpoint, we always strive to offer you the best possible product. Please be assured that these black and brown spots do not pose any health risk. It is thus not harmful for a consumer to eat a potato with a black spot. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact me.
Subject: Mercadona: Consumer Complaint (L-800)

TextBody: Hello Ricardo Thank you for informing us about the issue reported here below. We have well received your complaint and have registered it in our system as reference 28104. Based on the lotcode, we traced back the production day to the 07th of April 2024. Based on the video we have received, we can confirm this is a piece of sprout on the potato. Sprout can occur while the potatoes are being stored. Potatoes with sprout are still good for consumption, but the sprout should be removed. We notice that they tend to be more present on today as we are nearing the end of the potato season. I have checked the production and tasting records around the time of your complaint, and no remarks about sprout on potatoes have been noted. Normally this kind of defects should have been rejected by our optical sorters. But unfortunately no system can give us a 100% guarantee that all potatoes with sprout will be detected. We would like to apologize for the inconvenience and want to confirm that this is not harmful for human consumption. If you might have any other questions, do not hesitate to contact me.
Subject: Mercadona: Consumer Complaint  ( L-800)

TextBody: Bonjour Quentin, Le contrôle de la coupe est effectué toutes les demi-heures. Le lot de plainte a été emballé à 20h40 et nous avons effectué un contrôle à 20h57 et à 20h30. Lors de ces contrôles, la coupe était bonne. Vers 17 heures, nous avons constaté une coteau cassé, mais la production à peu près au moment de la pause a été bloqué et détruit. D'après nos dossiers, la coupe du produit emballé à 20h40 devrait être conforme aux normes et nous n'avons aucune explication sur le fait qu'elle soit encore trop épaisse. Il s'agit peut-être d'une constatation du client (le client pense que le produit est trop épais alors qu'il est conforme aux normes). Si vous souhaitez obtenir de plus amples informations, nous vous prions de bien vouloir nous donner plus de détails : - existe-t-il des photos montrant que le produit est trop épais ? - Le client dispose-t-il d'un autre lot qui est manifestement moins épais ? Dans l'affirmative, veuillez également indiquer le code du lot. - quelle quantité est trop épaisse ? S'agit-il d'un sac complet, de plusieurs sacs ou d'un certain nombre de frites provenant d'un seul sac ? Merci d'avance, Cordiallement, Kathleen Samyn Technical Sales Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message ---------------
Subject: Réclamation qualité Sysco France / Litige n° 24,2906 - 2629366

Gelieve ook de preventieve maatregelen mee te geven die door u worden genomen om deze klacht in de toekomst te vermijden. Indien u meent dat er een risico bestaat voor de algemene (voedsel)veiligheid, vragen we u om meteen over te gaan tot een risicoanalyse en ons de besluiten ervan mee te delen. TextBody: Hi Marlies, As part of Asda’s routine due diligence testing a nutritional analysis has been completed on the Straight Cut Chips and the total fats have come back out of spec. The analysed results on fats have come back lower than the on-pack claims; total fats is 1.9g vs. pack claim of 3.29g, and this difference is greater than the tolerance allowed in legislation – the test certificate is attached for reference. Summary of the results is also below: [cid:image001.png@01DAB1D6.A4C5B8F0] Please can you investigate this OOS result and provide a comprehensive response using the attached SGS OOS follow-up template on what might have caused this variation along with all relevant production docs to support? The date code of the product that was tested is – BB 06/09/2025, G08 24 067 22:33. The last nutrition verification certificate that we hold on file for this product is dated August 2023. Do you have any of your own more recent ‘as consumed’ nutrition analysis for the product that you can send to support the BOP nutrition? Please can you provide your initial response on the above by 3pm on Tuesday 4th June. Let me know if you have any questions. Many thanks, Dan [cid:image085537.png@597E1F50.1B10F456] [Fullers Foods Facebook]<https://www.facebook.com/fullersfoods> [Fullers Foods Instagram]<https://www.instagram.com/fullersfoods/> [Fullers Foods LinkedIn]<https://www.linkedin.com/company/fullers-foods-plc/> Daniel Taylor​​​​ Senior Technical Manager [cid:image431687.png@D8DE5340.365A1F84] +44 7881 338652<tel:+44%207881%20338652> [cid:image467251.png@0F69246B.E5D4B9EB] +44 1134 579945<tel:+44%201134%20579945> [cid:image389958.png@138EF513.7228078F] https://fullersfoods.com<https://fullersfoodsplc.com/> [cid:image321972.png@12B5C5E3.37424CB4] daniel.taylor@fullersfoods.com<mailto:daniel.taylor@fullersfoods.com> MY EMAIL ADDRESS HAS CHANGED TO @fullersfoods.com 31 Westgate, Leeds, LS1 2RA, United Kingdom Note: This email has been sent from a member of Fullers Foods International Limited and is confidential and intended solely for the use of the individual to whom it is addressed. TextBody: Dear Vinicius, We have registered it in our system under ticket number 00028274. You are correct, this complaint should not be possible due to our checkweigher. See below. Batch information: Lotcode : G03233471220 Packaging day : 13/12/2023 Our high-tech packaging lines are automatically controlled to ensure the precise net weight per bag, in accordance with EU standards. As part of the packaging process, each packaging line is equipped with two check weighers. One weigher checks the weight of each individual bag, while the other verifies the weight of each filled carton (trade unit). If a bag or carton is underweight, it is automatically rejected. Additionally, the packaging operators check the proper functioning of the check weigher during each shift. The average weight of the bags is also monitored for compliance, and all data from the packaging line (Garvens) is automatically recorded. We have conducted traceability checks, no remarks were made.We can confirm that the bags have been filled in accordance with EU standards, and any bags that did not meet these standards were removed from the production line. Can you please advise if the box contained 10 full bags and 1 empty one?This is the only explination I would have for this complaint. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: Claim 02903758 - Empty pack

TextBody: Hi Evelien, As I am sure Kathleen has made you aware Morrisons are very concerned about the number of defect complaints they are receiving for their roast potatoes. We had a similar issue last year for the product & the pattern is repeating. The product is the same as for ASDA & Tesco & I know they have had shared production runs, but these customers don’t have the same issue with complaints. Kathleen has made us aware of a project that is underway to improve the optical sorters to improve the rejections for defects on the roast potatoes we have made Morrisons aware that this is happening & have asked for further details of the scope & aim of this project when the person responsible is back from their holiday. Given the work on the optical sorter from what date code can we expect improved product to be seen by the Morrisons customer? Paul Montgomery would like to visit Tilburg as soon as possible given the numbers of complaints when this product is being produced. Please can you advise a suitable date for this visit?
Subject: RE: 40313499 Morrisons FB Complaint - Roast Potatoes 800g 600477

TextBody: Dear Vinicius, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00028225. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : D04233310829 Packaging day : 27/11/2023 I would like to reassure you that during the packing process, we conduct quality checks. Our team tests the seals of the bags on an hourly basis. A box is removed from the packaging line, and all bags are meticulously inspected to ensure that the seals are properly closed. These inspection results are recorded in our Quality documents. In light of the concerns you raised, we have conducted an investigation into the packaging checks for the particular batch. The bag was checked at 8h20. No remarks were made. This is wy we believe this is an isolated issue. We regret any inconvenience this issue may have caused you or your customer. We take this matter seriously and are committed to preventing such incidents in the future. Should you require any further information or assistance, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Subject: Claim 02880438 - Sealing issue

TextBody: Dear Ana Škurina, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00027845. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : G0523 (BBD 05.10.2025) - G0124 (BBD 03.02.2026) - G0124 (BBD 11.04.2026) BBD: 05.10.2025 - 03.02.2026 - 11.04.2026 I would like to reassure you that during the packing process, we conduct quality checks. Our team tests the seals of the bags on an hourly basis. A box is removed from the packaging line, and all bags are meticulously inspected to ensure that the seals are properly closed. These inspection results are recorded in our Quality documents. In light of the concerns you raised, we have conducted an investigation into the packaging checks for the particular batch and we conclude that this is an isolated case. We regret any inconvenience this issue may have caused you or your customer. We take this matter seriously and are committed to preventing such incidents in the future. Should you require any further information or assistance, please do not hesitate to contact us. You will receive a credit note shortly.

TextBody: Dear Vinicius, We have registered it in our system under ticket number 00028274. You are correct, this complaint should not be possible due to our checkweigher. See below. Batch information: Lotcode : G03233471220 Packaging day : 13/12/2023 Our high-tech packaging lines are automatically controlled to ensure the precise net weight per bag, in accordance with EU standards. As part of the packaging process, each packaging line is equipped with two check weighers. One weigher checks the weight of each individual bag, while the other verifies the weight of each filled carton (trade unit). If a bag or carton is underweight, it is automatically rejected. Additionally, the packaging operators check the proper functioning of the check weigher during each shift. The average weight of the bags is also monitored for compliance, and all data from the packaging line (Garvens) is automatically recorded. We have conducted traceability checks, no remarks were made.We can confirm that the bags have been filled in accordance with EU standards, and any bags that did not meet these standards were removed from the production line. Can you please advise if the box contained 10 full bags and 1 empty one?This is the only explination I would have for this complaint. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: Claim 02903758 - Empty pack

TextBody: Cher / Chère Edouard Cailette , Nous vous remercions de nous avoir informé de ce sujet, que nous avons immédiatement enregistré dans notre système sous le numéro de ticket 00027986. Nous sommes désolés d'apprendre que votre client n'était pas satisfait de la qualité de cette série. La qualité de nos produits est d'une importance capitale pour nous, et nous sommes déterminés à résoudre cette question. Informations sur le batch: Lotcode : D012410418 Date de Production: Compte tenu de notre processus de production, qui comprend des laveuses de pommes de terre, de l'eau de traitement, des blanchisseuses, des friteuses, et plus encore, il est très improbable que cet insecte ait pu parcourir l'ensemble de notre processus de production sans être détecté et retiré. Nous sommes convaincus qu'une contamination de cette nature aurait été identifiée à plusieurs étapes de la production. Par conséquent, nous soupçonnons que la contamination a pu se produire après la phase de friture. Il est possible qu'un insecte soit entré dans notre environnement de production et se soit involontairement attaché aux frites avant l'emballage. Il est important de noter que nous disposons d'un système rigoureux de lutte antiparasitaire pour empêcher l'entrée d'insectes et de rongeurs dans l'usine. Toutes les portes doivent impérativement rester fermées en permanence, et nous effectuons une surveillance constante de ces contrôles. J'ai déjà entamé le processus d'acquisition d'informations sur la lutte antiparasitaire autour de la date de production, . Actuellement, nos résultats en matière de contrôle qualité ne révèlent rien d'anormal. Malheureusement, il semble que, malgré nos efforts, nous n'ayons pas réussi à prévenir la contamination dans ce cas, et nous tenons à nous en excuser. Si vous ou votre client avez besoin de plus d'informations, n'hésitez pas à nous contacter. Si vous avez besoin de plus d'infos, merci de me fournir la photo concernée. Cordialement, Sarah Sarah Detailleur Customer Experience Officer Agristo nv P +32 56 54 11 65 M + 0498 74 13 14 --------------- Original Message ---------------

TextBody: Thank you, Sarah. We appreciate the team’s immediate attention to this. I’m sharing some additional pictures from this morning’s delivery. Please also see picture with the open case with 3 sleeves of HB missing. The case was loaded like that. How could that have happened? @Sonja <mailto:Sonja.Deleersnijder@agristo.com> thank you for your call earlier today. As discussed, the customer would be looking for answers on the following. We should be prepared with answers to this tomorrow morning please. * Does the expedition team have authorization/capability to reject pallets upon loading? (considering a zero tolerance policy for damaged cases/pallets) * And where would the rejected pallets go? Do the loading docks have a dedicated area for repacking/restacking/reworking? (temp controlled space) * OR do they have capability to pick new pallet(s)? How long would it take to pick new missing pallet(s)? 10-20 min or 2hr? Is it reasonable to assume the haulier can wait? * Who does the expedition team communicate with when they see physical damages? Is it escalated to supervisor? Is there a supervisor walking the loading dock at all times? At the end of the day, customer believes we need to tighten up oversight of the expedition team. The proposed corrective measures might do the trick. Thank you for checking feasibility. * Supervisors on the floor for frequent spot checks * Agristo Customer service team drop in for random spot checks * Have haulier spot check (DBS/RCL) – important we inspect along the way during container loading, not just before doors are closed, as damages are not typically at the doors, but in the middle pallets * Declare empty boxes on PL & Invoice * Ensure capability to reject and pick new pallets Thank you <https://protect.checkpoint.com/v2/___http://www.ardovlm.com/___.YzJlOmFncmlzdG86YzpvOjY5MWRlMTU0NmE5NjNiOGZmNGVhNzVhNmY3OGFhYzFjOjY6Zjk4Yjo2ZTA4NWEyMjg1YTA4YzhmNzBkNjg5ZDMzNzIwNzA1MGE2MWE5MmU2OGMwNTIwOTg4NzhlMWU4YzRmZjg4NzM4Omg6Rg> Kayla Karabachian Business Unit Manager – Industry/Food Service 1675 Blvd. Saint-Regis, Dollard-des-ormeaux, QC, H9B 3H7 T: (514) 825-9346 | F: (514) 426-5977 From: Sarah Detailleur <Sarah.Detailleur@agristo.com> Sent: Wednesday, May 29, 2024 12:13 PM To: Kayla Karabachian <kayla.karabachian@ardo.com>; Sophie François <Sophie.Francois@agristo.com>; Sophie Rondou <Sophie.Rondou@agristo.com> Cc: Louise Regnier <Louise.Regnier@agristo.com>; Jeff Preston <Jeff.Preston@ardo.com>; Julia Melnyk <Julia.Melnyk@ardo.com> Subject: RE: Reddy Raw PO 755808 (VF3314) CAUTION: This email originated from outside of the organization. TextBody: Good morning Clare, We received the following answer by our production planners: This week we have the last run of the HNA F with the old crop. The next run will only be again with the new harvest probably in week 30 or week 32. I dare not say for sure yet because it is not yet known when new harvest starts. Maybe we can set up a teams meeting to discuss this with Mr Montgomery as a visit during production of this article is currently impossible? Next week we will send you more information when we have asked our product engineer for more feedback as he is on holiday this week. We will keep you posted.
Subject: RE: 40313499 Morrisons FB Complaint - Roast Potatoes 800g 600477

TextBody: Dear Samantha Thank you for your email. I am concerned to hear about your recent purchase. We strive to ensure that all products supplied to us are of a standard and quality you would expect from Farmfoods. I have today forwarded your comments to the supplier of this product for them to look into further. If you do still have the original packaging and can let me know the batch code, I can also pass that on to help with their investigation. In the meantime, please accept my sincere apologies for the distress and inconvenience this must have caused. I would like to send you, with our compliments, a Farmfoods voucher as a gesture of goodwill. I would also like to enclose a self-addressed envelope for safe return of the mentioned object. Once received, I will forward this to the supplier to further aid their investigation. I will send this in today’s post to the address provided in your email. I do hope that you will continue to shop at Farmfoods as we do value your custom.
Subject: Ref: 324042TH Customer Enquiry

TextBody: Geachte, Bedankt dat u deze kwestie onder onze aandacht heeft gebracht. We hebben het onmiddellijk in ons systeem geregistreerd onder ticketnummer 00028258. Het spijt ons te horen dat uw klant niet tevreden was over de kwaliteit van onze producten. De kwaliteit van onze producten is voor ons van het allergrootste belang en wij doen er alles aan om deze kwestie op te lossen. Badinformatie: Lotcode: D02240821533 Inpakdag: 22/03/2024 Op basis van de lotcode hebben wij onze productiegegevens en kwaliteitsdocumenten voor deze specifieke batch grondig onderzocht. Er is geen melding gemaakt over vreemde blauwe stukjes in het product. Vermoedelijk gaat het hier over transportband of blauwe liner stukjes. Voor verder onderzoek, heb ik de foto's doorgestuurd naar onze kwaliteitsmanager om achter te halen wat de oorzaak hiervan zou zijn. Eenmaal ik haar feedback heb, zal ik u verder inlichten over het onderzoek. In tussentijd, indien u verder vragen hebt, contacteer mij gerust. Met vriendelijke groeten Sandrine Van Bockstael Technical Sales Officer Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: CSMGT [customer.servicemanagement@colruytgroup.com] Sent: 29/05/2024 16:02 To: sarah.segers1@colruyt.be; wouter.claerhout@agristo.com; claims@agristo.com; veerle.vanhecke@colruytgroup.com Cc: servicenow.confidential@colruytgroup.com Subject: CMPL0047441 - Klacht - ART 22160 BONI aardappelkroketten oven 1kg CMPL0047441 - Klacht - ART 22160 BONI aardappelkroketten oven 1kg Beste leverancier, Op 29-05-2024 14:33:02 CEST ontvingen wij onderstaande klacht: Klachtinformatie: CLP-Aankoop Klachtnummer: CMPL0047441 Artikel: 22160 - BONI aardappelkroketten oven 1kg Lotcode: D02 24 082 15:33 Klacht: "Kroketten zien blauw." Wij vragen u om op basis van de doorgestuurde gegevens na te gaan welke oorzaken van uw kant mogelijks aan de basis liggen van deze klacht. Gelieve ook de preventieve maatregelen mee te geven die door u worden genomen om deze klacht in de toekomst te vermijden. Indien u meent dat er een risico bestaat voor de algemene (voedsel)veiligheid, vragen we u om meteen over te gaan tot een risicoanalyse en ons de besluiten ervan mee te delen. Op die manier kunnen ook wij direct de nodige maatregelen treffen en de betrokkenen correct informeren. Graag hadden wij een eerste reactie uiterlijk binnen de 48u ontvangen na ontvangst van deze klacht. Met vriendelijke groeten, Camille Muller Quality Officer Service Center Quality Product camille.muller@colruytgroup.com T +32 (0)2 363 55 45 Edingensesteenweg 196 - 1500 Halle www.colruytgroup.com LinkedIn Twitter Ref:MSG28560049_J274r255nobuCmMMEko

TextBody: Cher , Nous vous remercions de nous avoir informé de ce sujet, que nous avons immédiatement enregistré dans notre système sous le numéro de ticket 00028045. Nous sommes désolés d'apprendre que votre client n'était pas satisfait de la qualité de cette production. La qualité de nos produits est d'une importance capitale pour nous, et nous sommes déterminés à résoudre cette question. TextBody: Bonjour, A la suite des différentes commandes livrées au cours du mois de avril 2024, nous avons constaté, sur la base du contrat logistique qui nous unit, des défauts de performances logistiques de votre part. Afin de démontrer ces manquements, vous trouverez en pièce jointe, à titre de preuve, une extraction du logiciel de gestion. Conformément au paragraphe D de la Foire Aux Questions portant sur les lignes directrices en matière de pénalités logistiques, « une photographie, une capture écran du logiciel » font partie des preuves matérialisant le manquement. Le préjudice lié à ces défauts de performance logistique est détaillé dans les pièces jointes. Le respect des niveaux de performance convenus dans notre contrat logistique permet d'assurer un taux de service optimal de livraison auprès de nos Points de Vente, permettant ainsi d’éviter tout manquement engendrant un manque à gagner à la revente en raison de l’indisponibilité de la marchandise en temps et heure. Nous vous rappelons que vous disposez d'un délai de 30 jours à compter de la réception de cet avis de pénalités pour en contrôler le bien-fondé et nous transmettre vos remarques. TextBody: Geachte, Bedankt dat u deze kwestie onder onze aandacht heeft gebracht. We hebben het onmiddellijk in ons systeem geregistreerd onder ticketnummer 00026998. Het spijt ons te horen dat uw klant niet tevreden was over de kwaliteit van onze producten. De kwaliteit van onze producten is voor ons van het allergrootste belang en wij doen er alles aan om deze kwestie op te lossen. Batchinformatie: Lotcode: D02240822041 Inpakdag: 22/03/2024 Deze klacht is gerelateerd aan jullie klacht CMPL0047441. Hierbij loopt er verder onderzoek door onze kwaliteitsmanager. Het gaat hier vermoedelijk over blauw plastiek uit onze productie. Op basis van de foto's zal er verder onderzoek lopen, over wat precies de oorzaak is van dit blauw plastiek. Hierbij wil ik de klant geruststellen dat er geen gevolgen zullen zijn door het eten hiervan. Wel zullen wel onze uiterste best doen om de oorzaak te achterhalen en gepaste maatregelen te nemen. In tussentijd, indien u verder vragen hebt, contacteer mij gerust. Nogmaals onze excuses voor het ongemak. We should be prepared with answers to this tomorrow morning please. * Does the expedition team have authorization/capability to reject pallets upon loading? (considering a zero tolerance policy for damaged cases/pallets) * And where would the rejected pallets go? Do the loading docks have a dedicated area for repacking/restacking/reworking? (temp controlled space) * OR do they have capability to pick new pallet(s)? How long would it take to pick new missing pallet(s)? 10-20 min or 2hr? Is it reasonable to assume the haulier can wait? * Who does the expedition team communicate with when they see physical damages? Is it escalated to supervisor? Is there a supervisor walking the loading dock at all times? At the end of the day, customer believes we need to tighten up oversight of the expedition team. TextBody: Bonjour, Je m'excuse pour le retard. Nous avons registré ce non-confirmité sous la référence 00028487. Concernant la matière sèche des pommes noisettes, j'ai eu la réponse qu'il ne peuvent pas adapter le taux de matière sèche pendant la production. Tout dépend du premix qui est livré et celui ci contrôle le taux de matière sèche. Sachez que la matière sèche n’est pas un taux fix et peut varier dans la saison ou par batch de pommes de terre. Le taux matière sèche est un paramètre inférieur chez les spécialités de pommes de terre. La matière sèche n’a pas un grand impact sur le texture d’une pomme noisette. Chez Agristo, le service qualité teste toutes les heures les paramètres organoleptiques et le lendemain il y a un panel qui aussi goûte les pommes noisettes après une production. TextBody: Hi Melanie, I reviewed the pictures. This also surprises me. First, I can confirm that the strength of the outer cases did not change. My first question would be if there were already this kind of issues in the past. But I see you already confirmed this is not the case. A possibility can be that the outer case was more exposed to humidity then normal. However, it is strange that it only concerns one case then. For the moment it is difficult to supply a root cause or corrective action since this has never happened in the past. I would assume this is an isolated case. I see that the bags inside are still ok. If this would not be the case, you can sent us a note for affected bags due to this issue. Please let us know if you would receive more claims of this sort in the future! In the future you can sent all your claims to claims@agristo.com <mailto:claims@agristo.com> . When I am on leave these kinds of complaints are then easily picked up by my colleagues! Thank you for your understanding. TextBody: Hi Ciara, Our production engineer has come back to me on your below questions. Was the optical sorter functioning correctly during production? The optical sorters (Triplus, Veryx and Pulsar) operated correctly (no failures or other anomalies reported in the production log). Would the residue on the FB prevent the optical sorter from detecting it? Since the material is not recognised, it is in all likelihood from a potato delivery. Such material is normally emitted by the Triplus. We will test this again with the received material. Please find the quality analyses report for the finisched product attached. I have requested the other report to the production responsibles, as soon as I get more information on this, I will send it through.
Subject: SERIOUS 2503002 Tesco FB Complaint - Spicy Potato Wedges 750g 600413

TextBody: Geachte, Mijn collega meldde dat u geprobeerd heeft om Agristo te contacteren in verband met deze klacht en u doorverwezen werd naar de kwaliteitsdienst van Nazareth. In tussentijd heb ik de kwaliteitsmanager gehoord. Ze heeft de status van haar onderzoek doorgegeven. Zoals gemeld, de kwaliteitsrapporten hebben geen melding gegeven van vreemde blauwe stukjes in het product tijdens deze batch. Tijdens de betreffende productiedag hebben we ook geen incidenten gehad met gebroken transportbanden of andere downtimes en hebben we geen product geblokkeerd omwille van vreemde stukjes. Voorlopig kunnen we de oorsprong van deze stukjes niet achterhalen. Voor verder onderzoek zijn we onze retentiestalen aan het uithalen. Deze zullen we uitvoerig onderzoeken om te bekijken of we hetzelfde beeld zien als jullie klanten. Heeft de klant vermeld of het over harde of zachte stukjes gaat? Zou er mogelijkheid zijn om deze stukjes terug te verkrijgen zodat we deze kunnen analyseren? Van zodra ik de documenten heb van het onderzoek, stuur ik deze door naar u, samen met de foto's van onderzoek van de retentiestalen. Had u graag een call ingepland om deze klacht te bespreken? Ik geef u alvast mijn mobiele telefoonnummer, voor verder contact: +32 498 60 12 06. Ik sta tot uw beschikking voor verder vragen. Met vriendelijke groeten Sandrine Van Bockstael Technical Sales Officer Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message ---------------

TextBody: Beste, Wij hebben de eerste klacht met nummer CMPL0046381 ook ontvangen via het Federaal Voedselagentschap. Op basis van foto's en beschrijving van de 2 klachten die wij ontvangen hebben via de consumenten kunnen wij ervan uitgaan dat deze klachten inderdaad gelinkt zijn aan elkaar. Jullie geven mee dat het vermoedelijk gaat over blauwe plastiek uit jullie productie. Is dit harde of zachte plastiek? Kan het scherpe randjes hebben en dus zou er een gevaar kunnen zijn voor de consument? Volgende lotcodes werden meegegeven in de klachten: "D02240822041" + "D0224082 15:33" Wij vermoeden dat dit lot D0224082 is en het uur van productie betreft, dus 15:33 en 20:41. Klopt dit? Zoja, dan gaat dit niet over een korte tijdspanne maar is het probleem vermoedelijk groter? Op basis van deze info hebben wij de paletten die geleverd werden in onze DC met THT 21-03-2026 geblokkeerd. Deze paletten hebben verschillende leverdata bij ons, nl. 22/05/2024, 27/05/2024 en 30/05/2024. Op welke datum werden de paletten met lot D0224082 geleverd bij ons in DC? Of hebben deze paletten ook allemaal dezelfde lotcode? Actie: op basis van deze klachten zijn wij genoodzaakt om de betrokken THT 21-06-2026 die reeds in ons winkels aanwezig is uit verkoop te nemen. Gelieve ons zo spoedig mogelijk om de hoogte te brengen indien jullie info hebben die het mogelijk maken om de uitverkoopname te beperken. Kunnen jullie ons feedback bezorgen of jullie de paletten die in onze DC geblokkeerd werden retour wensen te nemen? Alvast bedankt voor jullie spoedige reactie. Met vriendelijke groeten - Sincères salutations -
Subject: CMPL0047441 - Klacht - ART 22160 BONI aardappelkroketten oven 1kg

TextBody: Geachte, Deze ochtend hebben we een meeting met onze groep kwaliteitsmanager en de plant kwaliteitsmanager over deze claims. Hierbij zullen we de retracering doen van de paletten. Ik stuur u daarna een excel door met de betrokken paletten en SSCC codes en de daarbij horende order- en leveringsdetails. In tussentijd worden de retentiestalen ontdooid van het betrokken bakorder; zodat we deze volledig kunnen ontleden om te zien of we blauwe deeltjes opmerken. Zoals eerder gemeld, heeft onze kwaliteitsmedewerker tijdens de uurlijkse staalafnames op de desbetreffende productiedag geen problemen opgemerkt, en kunnen we niet afleiden wat de oorzaak is en als het over een wijdverspreid probleem gaat. Voor alsnog kunnen we niet bepalen indien het over hard of zacht plastiek gaat. Hiervoor hadden we graag verder onderzoek gedaan. Daarom hadden we graag bekeken of Colruyt of de eindconsument of FAVV deze stukjes in het bezit heeft en indien we deze met een dringende koerier kunnen ophalen. Zou u dit kunnen navragen aub? TextBody: Geachte, Deze ochtend hebben we een meeting met onze groep kwaliteitsmanager en de plant kwaliteitsmanager over deze claims. Hierbij zullen we de retracering doen van de paletten. Ik stuur u daarna een excel door met de betrokken paletten en SSCC codes en de daarbij horende order- en leveringsdetails. In tussentijd worden de retentiestalen ontdooid van het betrokken bakorder; zodat we deze volledig kunnen ontleden om te zien of we blauwe deeltjes opmerken. Zoals eerder gemeld, heeft onze kwaliteitsmedewerker tijdens de uurlijkse staalafnames op de desbetreffende productiedag geen problemen opgemerkt, en kunnen we niet afleiden wat de oorzaak is en als het over een wijdverspreid probleem gaat. Voor alsnog kunnen we niet bepalen indien het over hard of zacht plastiek gaat. Hiervoor hadden we graag verder onderzoek gedaan. Daarom hadden we graag bekeken of Colruyt of de eindconsument of FAVV deze stukjes in het bezit heeft en indien we deze met een dringende koerier kunnen ophalen. Zou u dit kunnen navragen aub? Bel mij gerust op bij verder vragen op het nummer 0498 60 12 06. Met vriendelijke groeten [image] Sandrine Van Bockstael Technical Sales Officer Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message ---------------
Subject: CMPL0047441 - Klacht - ART 22160 BONI aardappelkroketten oven 1kg

TextBody: Madame, Monsieur, Nous avons trouvé un accord définissant les principes et les conditions logistiques et techniques qui s’appliquent entre nos deux sociétés. La loi n° 2023-221 du 30 mars 2023 poursuit les objectifs déjà présents dans la loi EGALIM 1 et 2. Cette loi, souvent désignée EGALIM 3, a été publiée au Journal officiel du 31 mars 2023. A ce titre, nous vous prions de trouver les datas indemnités logistiques retard et qualité de avril 2024, joints au présent courrier, lequel fait suite à nos différents échanges. Ce qui a pour objet de lancer la période d’échanges contradictoires en perspectives de trouver un accord sur le montant de réparation du préjudice. Nous vous rappelons que vous disposez d'un délai de 30 jours à compter de la réception de cet avis de pénalités pour en contrôler le bien-fondé et nous transmettre vos remarques. Merci de nous retourner vos analyses contradictoires associées à cette extraction. Au retour de vos remarques, lors d’échanges contradictoires, nous prendrons en compte les éléments justifiés et documentés que vous mentionneriez afin d’obtenir un accord avant établissement d’une facturation. Nous restons à votre disposition pour toute question et pour étudier avec vous des moyens spécifiques afin d'améliorer votre performance logistique pour nos prochaines commandes. Nous vous remercions de bien vouloir adresser vos retours à l'adresse mail : itmlai_negociations_logistiques@mousquetaires.com et à votre négociateur de dossier : - Fatyne BOUFOUS - fatyne.boufous@mousquetaires.com : Frais non laitier (volailles, œuf, traiteur, charcuterie, traiteur de la mer, viandes) - Priscillia LUZOLO - priscillia.luzolo@mousquetaires.com : DPH (Parfumerie, entretien et Hygiène) & Epicerie Salée - Marylise GOBIN - marylise.gobin@mousquetaires.com : Epicerie Sucrée / PPI & Animaux - Chloé MAYALA - chloe.mayala@mousquetaires.com : Vins & Champagnes, BNA, Bière, Alcools & Gel - Faustine BOSIO - faustine.bosio@mousquetaires.com : Frais Laitier - Carine GALLETTE - carine.gallette@mousquetaires.com : Maison/Textile Nous vous prions de croire, Madame, Monsieur, à l’expression de notre considération distinguée. TextBody: Dear Mya san, Following our telephone conversation, I have talked to one of our process engineers. Please note that for foreign bodies and product clumps, we do not adjust the settings of the optical sorter. These settings have been determined in close collaboration with the company that installs the optical sorters and has extensive knowledge about the machine, and are not changed. In most of the cases, these settings are working fine and will reject the product clumps. As also mentioned over the phone, however, it is always possible that one of these product clumps is not rejected. There can be several reasons for this: The product clump is under a "pile" of fries and is not detected. The product clump is detected, but is not properly rejected and is "shot" back in the "good" product flow, instead of being rejected to the "bad" product flow. That being said, for defects (black, brown, green or blue spots on the product), we can and do adjust the settings of the optical sorter in between runs (depending of the recipe we are producing) and during the run if this is deemed necessary (for example when our Quality Control staff notices that we are high in defects, we can adjust the settings of the optical sorter and make it "stricter"). Our production team knows the standard, minimum and maximum values they can set. I hope to have informed you sufficiently, and remain at your disposal for any further information.
Subject: RE: [Ticket: 124753] Claim:503

TextBody: Beste allen, Zonet hebben Sandrine en ik met Veerle Vanhecke gebeld. Een heel rustige dame … De klachten komen van 2 consumenten uit verschillende winkels. Beide klachten zijn ook aan het FAVV gemeld. Zij nemen nu contact op met de consument om te zien of we het product retour kunnen krijgen. Ik verwacht niet dat we dit vandaag nog zullen zien. TextBody: Goede middag, Het gaat niet echt om blokkeren van het product, er wordt slechts effectief geblokkeerd wanneer meer dan 10% daadwerkelijk defects heeft/niet conform is. Op het moment van opstart wordt de machine - indien nodig bijgestuurd - en is er dus steeds een visuele controle. Bij opstart kan men er dan ook voor kiezen om een gedeelte rechtstreeks naar de afvalbak te sturen. Daarna baseren we ons verder op de controles die we elk uur uitvoeren, waarbij alle parameters van het product volgens vooropgestelde specificatie worden gecontroleerd. Helaas is het hierbij dus mogelijk dat enkele misvormde kroketten aan ons monitoringssysteem ontsnappen. TextBody: Dear Terek Hazell , Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00028362. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Bath information: Production day : After reviewing the picture and description, it appears that the foreign body in question is a clump of fat from the oven. We want to assure you that we have a regular visual inspection of the oven every hour. If excessive accumulation is observed, our team takes immediate action to clean the oven. Based on the lotcode, we have conducted an investigation into our production records and quality documents for this specific batch. There were no remarks registered in the quality control sheets. We are confident that this complaint is an isolated incident and not widespread. To prevent such occurrences, we will hold discussions with our production team to enhance their focus on the visual inspection of the oven. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.

TextBody: Dear, We have well received your below notification. First of all, I wish to explain the difference between the 2 products. Although at first glance, the Green Tape (coated salted product) may look quite similar to the White Tape (batter product), there Is a clear difference. You will notice the ingredient declaration is completely different as for the White product we are using Batter, which ensures product to remain very crispy for a longer period of time. Consumer experience may be different as a result. By this, of course, we do not mean that one product is better than the other, both are produced to high predefined standards. Getting back to the reason for your complaint, I noticed your complaint is related to 2 different lotcodes/batches: LOT C01 24 131 0959 Production day: 10th May LOT C05 24 035 0416 Production day: 4th February For the batch which has been produced beginning of May, it may occur that some darken faster, which could be explained to the increased presence of natural sugars at the end of the potato season. Having checked the QC records of this particular batch, I did notice an increase of sugar points, which were still within specification. Concerning the batch which has been produced on the 4th of February, I noticed your complaint is linked to the start-up of the production run. In the QC records it is shown that in the beginning we were indeed against the upper limit concerning sugar points, as a result of which production parameters were adjusted. On a subsequent check, we see the number of sugar points visibly decreasing and this remains throughout the rest of the run. Based on the above investigation and after checking with internally, we can grant you a credit note for the amount of 9 outer cases. Our apologies for the inconveniences. Hope this info serves you well,
Subject: FW: Golden green tape chips.

TextBody: Dear Pieter Lapierre san, Thank you for your reply. I have the following additional questions. Is the size of the perforation 2 cm? According to your documents, the problematic quantity this time seems to be 2,800 cartons. Is it possible to narrow down the scope of the problem even a little? We may have to sort them out here. Also, after discussing this with the packaging manager, please let us know what new measures you plan to take in the future. Yuga From: Agristo Claims <claims@agristo.com> Sent: Thursday, May 30, 2024 10:21 PM To: quality-improvement(kobebussan) <quality-improvement@kobebussan.co.jp> Cc: Neviani Ilaria(kobebussan) <neviani@kobebussan.co.jp>; Atsushi Karita(kobebussan) <karita@kobebussan.co.jp>; Noriyoshi Miki(kobebussan) <miki@kobebussan.co.jp>; Kenji Inada(kobebussan) <k.inada@kobebussan.co.jp>; Makoto Nakahara(kobebussan) <nakahara@kobebussan.co.jp>; line.cabbeke@agristo.com; Takuya Sakai(kobebussan) <sakai@kobebussan.co.jp> Subject: RE: [Request for confirmation] Claim Report 396716 [597:Agristo(ヘ゛ルキ゛ー)]◆ Dear Yuga san, Enclosed you can find an overview of the goods that have been produced, including the batch code, expiry date, order number and invoice number. As this was evident on the pictures you kindly shared, we are sure that this kind of perforation has been used on packing line D05. As you can see on the overview, however, 3 pallets were also packed on packing line D07 on this day. Unfortunately, as we do not have reference samples from this packing line, we can't tell if this kind of perforation has been used on this packing line D07 as well or not. Once again our sincere apologies for this. I have escalated this matter internally. If you need any further information, please do not hesitate to contact me.

TextBody: Dear Pieter I hope this email finds you well. Thank you for your reply. We shared the info with the custom brokers, and they checked the documents. Here below you may find some questions from them: 1) The production flow chart has AT1 and AT2. Which process do you follow for this item? AT1 or AT2? 2) By “salt bath” what do you mean? What kind of process is it? Also, is there any remaining salt (residue) in the final product? 3) In the last page of the flowchart, there is “fat application”. How do you apply fat? Is the palm oil indicated at this point, the one that you indicated in the ingredients (palm oil 2.7%)? 4) Are the other fat/oil used in this item? Thank you for your support. Looking forward to your reply.
Subject: Report of Difference Item -  INV: 90591509

TextBody: Dear, we've well received the foreign body. Please find below our investigation. Product Name: MCY 700G POT SHA GRILLED STK Product Codes: PLU 87633 Best Before or Use By date: 08 Dec 2024 Batch Code/Lot code: D06 22 346 08:24 Summary of complaint: 6 cm piece of hard blue plastic Supplier Comments How many packs were produced? 2340 CAR - 37440 units Line number Packaging line 6 Date of production D06 22 346 08:24 Daycode 346 = 12 december 2022 packaging order 1303702904 ICE BCSLG ,70 1 L60 (311566) van 12/12/2022 en 13/12/2022 Were any issues or non-conformances recorded for this production; including foreign body controls and monitoring equipment? Originating from 2 production orders: 1301029373 BLK BDCRSAUL 1 SUN T FGS (311602) from 11/2022 1301029445 BLK BDCRSAUL 1 SUN T FGS (311602) from 11/2022 1 foreign body message during run: no similarities with particle found by customer. Particle was removed from product flow + installation in NZ was checked, no deviations were noted. No other comments in Patapp, no NCP's created. Please outline the controls in place to prevent foreign material entering products -inspections of chip sites Our production chip line is equipped with multiple sophisticated installations to remove foreign objects from the production line, such as: Stone remover Washer Hedghoge conveyor Salt baht Different optical sorters -visual inspection when tilting fries in the gratin mixer. Have you reviewed retained samples / taste panel records - any deviation to specification? no Are complaints recorded and monitored for Trending purposes? yes How are complaints communicated to Staff / Senior Team? KPI consultation moments + memo Could the root cause be identified? No Outline Corrective Actions - Provide copies as attachment to support investigation of any relevant records (as below- not limited too) Glass & Plastic Checks Production Records Foreign body detection checks (Metal detector, X-Ray, Filters, optical sorts) QC Checks Taste Panel /Retained Samples External Independent Laboratory Analysis Report – Iceland requirement for ALL glass complaints Our investigation when we received the piece: Particle received and viewed with production manager: appears to match the color of the blue plasic palettes used in our factory. The structure is previously ribbed, but lifting the pallets with the forks of the forklift could possibly cause burrs to come loose and give them a ribbed appearance. How can this get to the product? To season the product, octabins with unseasoned product are coming in from the other production cites. These are tipped into our mixing plant. During tilting, the pallet is also tilted. The chance is rather small, but not non-existent, that a loose piece of the pallet has ended up in the product flow. We believe their is no food safety risk as the piece was in the bag and not in the product. The piece had a bleu color so it's visible to the consumer. At your disposal for further questions.
Subject: Iceland Customer Product Complaint 03261201

TextBody: Beste lezer, Op het verzoek van PLUS Consumentenservice met referentienummer 240526-000042 heeft u zojuist de volgende reactie verstuurd: 3/6/2024 08:29 - Evelien Cremers Beste, Wij mochten onderstaande consumentenklacht met betrekking tot een vreemd voorwerp dat werd gevonden in de Plus Friet met schil in goede orde ontvangen. Het spijt ons te vernemen dat uw consument een negatieve ervaring had met een door Agristo geproduceerd artikel. Wij hechten immers het grootste belang aan de kwaliteit van onze producten en verpakkingen. Wij hebben deze melding in ons systeem geregistreerd onder ref. 28528. Aan de hand van de lotcode (G322327510:58) en de vervaldatum (01/10/2025) hebben wij kunnen achterhalen dat dit een productie betreft van 02/10/2023. We hebben de productiebladen en de kwaliteitscontroles van deze batch gecontroleerd – er werden geen anomalieën genoteerd. De volledige productie was conform. Het productieproces bevat veel fysieke en optische eliminatiestappen voor vreemde voorwerpen. Agristo probeert ook te investeren in alle nieuwe best practice technische oplossingen om vreemde voorwerpen te vermijden. Op basis van de foto's kunnen wij u bevestigen dat dit gaat om 2 stukjes opgehoopte afgebakken coating die vanuit de bakoven zijn losgekomen. De ovens worden op regelmatige gecontroleerd en gekuist zodoende deze stukken niet in de zak belanden. Daarnaast beschikken wij oven verschillende sorteert bedden die in normale omstandigheden deze stukken zouden moeten uitsorteren. Het ziet er naar uit dat ondanks onze harde inspanning er toch een stuk door de mazen van het net zijn gegaan. Waarvoor onze excuses. Mocht u nog vragen hebben dan horen wij het graag. Met vriendelijke groet, Evelien Cremers Uw antwoord zal, indien van toepassing, door PLUS Consumentenservice worden gebruikt om een antwoord richting de klant te formuleren. Mocht u nog vragen of opmerkingen hebben, neem dan gerust contact op met ons via 0800-222 44 43. Met vriendelijke groet, PLUS Consumentenservice
Subject: Melding PLUS Consumentenservice - 240526-000042 - Friet met schil bevatte 2 stukken aardappelsmurrie

TextBody: Bonjour, Nous avons bien reçu votre e-mail et l'avons enregistré sous le numéro de dossier 28500. En pièce jointe, vous trouverez le CMR et la liste de colisage de cet envoi. Les marchandises ont été produites sur notre site de production à Nazareth, puis envoyées à notre site de Wielsbeke, d'où elles sont parties vers chez vous. La température de nos produits lors du chargement est un point d'attention (CCP) basé sur notre analyse des risques. C'est pourquoi nous contrôlons la température à chaque chargement en insérant un thermomètre à sonde entre les boîtes d'une palette. Pour le chargement depuis Wielsbeke vers Pomona, une température de -19°C a été enregistrée (voir capture d'écran). Pour votre information : le signe moins ne fonctionne pas dans SAP, c'est pourquoi il est indiqué '19'. [Inline image URL : data:image/png;base64,
Subject: PPF OUEST:  URGENT - Anomalie produits - AGRISTO

TextBody: Dear Mya san, In reply to question number 1 and 2: I checked internally, but we cannot give any more details about the settings (values) of the optical sorter. First of all, this is business sensitive information which is not shared with third parties. Secondly, we don't see any added value in sharing these numbers. Unless somebody has extensive knowledge about these machines, the numbers won't say anything. Thirdly, these figures are not relevant to this complaint as this does not change whether there may be product clumps in the product or not. (The settings are only adjusted for defects, not for product clumps.) In reply to question number 3: As you know, every hour, a bag is taken from the packing line to check the quality we are producing. Our QC team does a number of quality checks (such as length, defects, temperature, smell, taste, etc.). Based on the results of the quality checks that have been carried out on defects, the team can decide to set the settings of the optical sorter "stricter". If the quality we are producing is fine, we don't need to adjust the optical sorter - if we are high on defects, we need to adjust the optical sorter. The number of times the optical sorter is checked / adjustes thus depends on the quality we are producing. I remain at your disposal should you require any further information.

TextBody: Dear, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00027274. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Bath information: Lotcode : C06232812127 Production day : 8/10/2023 There is a complete Quality Assurance system in place and the principles of HACCP are applied. This includes a full monitoring system on the production line. The finished products themselves are sampled every 60 minutes and examined for quality, including length and slivers. Full records of these and all the other checks are maintained. Based on the lotcode, we have conducted a thorough investigation into our production records and quality documents for this specific batch. Please see below the results of the check at 21h05 Length >50mm: 65.43% (min 60% = standard) Length <25mm: 1.56% (max6% = standard) Although the values in our hourly checks do not suggest issues, the pictures indeed show very short fries. I have issues a credit note for these 2 boxes. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: BRF Claim - Protocolo 2902682

TextBody: Dear, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00028083. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : G10231351539 Production day : 15/05/2023 Based on the provided pictures we have received, we can confirm this is a piece of sprout on the potato. Sprout can occur while the potatoes are being stored. Potatoes with sprout are still good for consumption, but the sprout should be removed. It appears that, despite our best efforts, some foreign material may have escaped our monitoring systems. Based on the lotcode, we have conducted a thorough investigation into our production records and quality documents for the specific batch. No remarks were made during production. We are confident that this complaint is not widespread. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: BRF Claim - Protocolo 2929283

TextBody: Dear, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00027273. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : G11230512112 Production day : 20/02/2023 Given our production process, which includes stone washers, process water, blanchers, fryers, and more, it's highly unlikely that this insect could have traversed our entire production process without being detected and removed. We are confident that any contamination of this nature would have been identified at multiple points during production. Therefore, we suspect that the contamination may have occurred after the frying process. It's possible that an insect entered our production environment and became unintentionally attached to the fries before packaging. It’s important to note that we have a rigorous pest control system to prevent the entry of insects and rodents into the factory environment All doors are strictly required to remain closed at all times, and we consistently monitor and inspect these controls. Based on the picture, I cannot confirm this is indeed an insect. Would it be possible to send this foreign body for further analysis? Should you or your customer require additional information, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Subject: BRF Claim - Protocolo 2912070

TextBody: Hello Clare, I contacted the service engineer who is responsible for this project on the Tilburg line. Scope: improve overall quality of cut potatoes mainly by having fewer major and critical defects in sold product. Start: early 2024 and is a one-year project, therefore runs until the end of 2024. Status: The optical sorter (Vyrex) emits potatoes with defects. As it is now: a visual check is done to see if defects are within spec (at least 2x per hours). The settings of the optical sorter are adjusted after the visual check if it appears that there are too many defects. During a visual check, only a few bags are checked. So, there is a delay in amending the Vyrex settings. The aim of the software is to automatically make adjustments to the optical sorter, if adjustments are needed, the settings of the Vyrex will automatically be amended, as soon as the software detects too many defects. Which means: from the moment there pass too many potatoes with critical/major defects--> Vyrex will automatically be amended so more potatoes will be rejected, settings will be more tight. But if settings are too tight, too much good potatoes will also be rejected. So as soon as defects are again within spec, Vyrex will automatically be amended. The software settings are mapped per bulk reference, so the software can automatically adjust the optical sorter settings per bulk reference as efficiently as possible. Setting the software settings is done by the service engineer. The fine-tuning of the software cannot be done by the operators, but must be done by the service engineer. Which means fine tuning can not be done on every production, but when the service engineer is available to work on the project. As this is done not only for the roast potatoes, but for all our bulk references on that production line, it is a time consuming project with a long lead time. We are still collecting data to assess the project's effectiveness. Hope this info helps,
Subject: RE: 40313499 Morrisons FB Complaint - Roast Potatoes 800g 600477

TextBody: Dear Aleksandra Štrbac , Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00028963. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : G3124035 Production day : 4/02/2024 Given our production process, which includes stone washers, process water, blanchers, fryers, and more, it's highly unlikely that this insect could have traversed our entire production process without being detected and removed. We are confident that any contamination of this nature would have been identified at multiple points during production. Therefore, we suspect that the contamination may have occurred after the frying process. It's possible that an insect entered our production environment and became unintentionally attached to the fries before packaging. It’s important to note that we have a rigorous pest control system to prevent the entry of insects and rodents into the factory environment All doors are strictly required to remain closed at all times, and we consistently monitor and inspect these controls I have already initiated the process of acquiring pest control information around the production date, 4/02/2024. As of now, our quality control results show nothing out of the ordinary. Unfortunately, it seems that despite our efforts, we failed to prevent contamination in this case, for which we wish to apologize. Should you or your customer require additional information, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Subject: Complaint, battered spicy jacket potato 750 g

Our Service team, currently consisting out of Technical Sales and Customer Service, is undergoing a transformative journey in the coming weeks and months, as we shift towards becoming a Customer Experience organization. This transformation is paired with some changes in customer allocation within both teams and in the way of communication. In concrete terms, for you, the following changes will take effect from today: * Personally, I will also become your point of contact, instead of Alexia, for everything related to orders, logistics and invoicing, next to the topics that I was already responsible for in my previous role as Technical Sales Officer (quality, packaging, specifications, …). * As from now on, you can direct all your service-related queries (so all questions and information which you used to send to Alexia and/or to myself) to the following central e-mail address: service@agristo.com<mailto:service@agristo.com>. TextBody: Dear, We have well received you below notification concerning our Harvest Basket Süsskartoffelpommes 500g. Declaration : Paprikaextract Our paprika oleoresin is categorized as an ‘flavouring preparation’ according EC 1334/2008 and is added to impart flavor. Net weight As part of the packaging process there are 2 check weighers on every packaging line. One which weighs every single bag and one which controls every filled carton (trade unit). When a bag or a carton weighs too little, either the bag or case will be rejected. Moreover, every shift the packaging operators checks the good functioning of the check weigher. Also the average weight of the bags is checked if conforming. All data from the packaging line (Garvens) is automatically registered. Attached you can find the automatic GarvensReport from the concerned production: Harvest Basket Süsskartoffelpommes 500g Agristo code : 312605 Lot: G24 23 314 11:44 Lot is referring to workcenter AW2 – Line 23 Packaging date: 9-11-2023 As you can see on the full report (attached), the average net weight has been reached during this production run = 500,2743g. We hope the above information has reassured you about the correct measures we follow. Please let me know you should have any further questions,
Subject: Stellungnahme Prüfbericht zu OP 2024/137234

TextBody: Hi Tareq, We would like to see a picture of the product within the bag, so we can determine if it is indeed bruises. Some explanation about bruises. With this type of defect, the defect shows more of a blue/brown discoloration as a result of cell damage due f.e. transport With bruises we divide it into 2 categories based on the color intensity of the punch blue/brown. Severely bruises count as a normal defect Light bruises: count as minor defect. Using the color chart helps determine whether the bruises are counted as a regular defect or a minor. If the color is present on the color card, the defect is counted as a normal defect. If the color is not present on the color card, so the color intensity is lighter, the defect is counted as a minor defect. COLOR CHART: blue and brown shades [cid:image002.png@01DAB656.2B656940] [cid:image003.png@01DAB656.2B656940]
Subject: RE: quality issue - Battered skin on Fries 10 x10 mm

TextBody: Evelien Mattheeuws Customer Service Officer UK & Europe P +32 56 54 10 68 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Agristo Claims [claims@agristo.com] Sent: 3/06/2024 16:15 To: clare.rowlands@fullersfoods.com Cc: ciara.sauvage@fullersfoods.com; evelien.mattheeuws@agristo.com Subject: RE: Morrisons Roast Potatoes Hello Clare, I contacted the service engineer who is responsible for this project on the Tilburg line. Scope: improve overall quality of cut potatoes mainly by having fewer major and critical defects in sold product. Start: early 2024 and is a one-year project, therefore runs until the end of 2024. Status: The optical sorter (Vyrex) emits potatoes with defects. As it is now: a visual check is done to see if defects are within spec (at least 2x per hours). The settings of the optical sorter are adjusted after the visual check if it appears that there are too many defects. During a visual check, only a few bags are checked. So, there is a delay in amending the Vyrex settings. The aim of the software is to automatically make adjustments to the optical sorter, if adjustments are needed, the settings of the Vyrex will automatically be amended, as soon as the software detects too many defects. Which means: from the moment there pass too many potatoes with critical/major defects--> Vyrex will automatically be amended so more potatoes will be rejected, settings will be more tight. But if settings are too tight, too much good potatoes will also be rejected. So as soon as defects are again within spec, Vyrex will automatically be amended. The software settings are mapped per bulk reference, so the software can automatically adjust the optical sorter settings per bulk reference as efficiently as possible. Setting the software settings is done by the service engineer. The fine-tuning of the software cannot be done by the operators, but must be done by the service engineer. Which means fine tuning can not be done on every production, but when the service engineer is available to work on the project. As this is done not only for the roast potatoes, but for all our bulk references on that production line, it is a time consuming project with a long lead time. We are still collecting data to assess the project's effectiveness. Hope this info helps,
Subject: RE: 40313499 Morrisons FB Complaint - Roast Potatoes 800g 600477

TextBody: Hi Mya San, please see below my response: 1. The production operator, shift supervisor and process engineer are trained 'on the job'. But at the start of their career in Agristo, they do get a theoretical training per part of the production line, including the area after freezing where the last optical sorter is located. There is no manual. Per product there is a standard setting of the optical sorter. Based on the hourly QC results they can adjust sensitivity. Please see attached a document I set up with more information. I hope this is helpfull! 2. Our intermediate cleaning is only with water (pressure 30bar) when we do a product change. The deparment cleaning is responsible for the claning,and they are with 2-3 people. The verfication is done by the shift supervisor of the line. I hope this information helps your customer close done this case.
Subject: RE: [Ticket: 124753] Claim:503

TextBody: Hi Dan, just for your info I want to share with you something we already shared on the NMR method 2 years ago: "Our experience over the last few years show the NMR method does not give a reliable result. It was always a method used commonly with milk powder which is a more homogeneous product but over the past few years appears to have been rolled out across other products such as our frozen potato products and is now commonly used in the UK. In fact we’ve had this exact same experience with another customer who was finding our products when tested weren’t in line with the nutrition in the spec/on pack. In this situation the results were as follows: - - Customer testing (NMR) = 4.9 - Spec/on pack claim = 9.7 - Same sample retested by customers lab but using Soxhlet method = 9.8 NB. For your interest I have attached a leaflet on NMR that does show results can come out lower but deemed to be not significant enough to worry about. Unfortunately we do not find this to be the case with our products. It also discusses how it is a preferred method as doesn’t require qualified staff and is a quicker method thus making it a much cheaper option, which explains a labs preference for using it." On potatoes: The variation depends on where we are in the season (early harvest, main harvest), as well as which potato variety is being used at that time. Since we work with natural products, it is not unusual to have natural variations in our products. Hopefully, the customer understands this as well. Of course, it is more meaningful to look at the overall picture and check the average from multiple analyses, rather than relying on just one analysis. Hope this helps!
Subject: FW: Asda Crinkle Cut Chips - Nutrition Out of Spec

TextBody: Dear Hagino, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00029355. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : A04233011124 Production day : 25/10/2023 By looking at the picture, we can confirm that this is some black fat coming from the baking oven. Apparently, some of the crum that can accumulate in the oven came loose and fell on a fry. Every hour the oven is visually checked. When there is too much fat accumulation, the oven is cleaned. It seems that this time, the oven was not cleaned on time and a clump of fat came loose. Normally these kind of clumps are removed by the optical sorter after freezing (before packing). It appears that, despite our best efforts, some foreign material may have escaped our monitoring system. Based on the batch code, we traced back the production day of this product to the 25th of October 2023. I have checked our records and there were no anomalies registered from this nature. Our hourly quality checks also do not mention any comment in this regard. We also haven’t received any similar complaints. That is why we think this is an isolated incident, for which we would like to apologize. I have escalated this complaint to our production team, so they pay more attention to the visual check of the oven. Please do not hesitate to contact me in case of further questions.
Subject: TOYOTA COMPLAINT FOR FRY WITH SUBSTANCES LOOKS MOLD
FW: KMM3_Incoming issue_Dehydrated potato flakes 3mm (008)_Agristo Belgium

TextBody: Bonjour, Nous avons bien reçu votre e-mail et l'avons enregistré sous le numéro de dossier 00029451. Nous regrettons que votre client ne soit pas satisfait de ce produit. Nous n'avons reçu aucune autre plainte à ce sujet. Les rapports de qualité horaires ne mentionnaient pas non plus de frites foncées. Après que les pommes de terre sont coupées en frites, elles sont brièvement blanchies, puis séchées, et pré-frites pendant environ 30 secondes à 180°C. Ces frites foncées ont probablement exceptionnellement passé le filtre du four de cuisson et ont été embarquées dans le four. L'huile dans le four de cuisson est continuellement filtrée, et sur la base des rapports du four de cuisson et des rapports de qualité horaires, nous sommes convaincus qu'il s'agit d'un incident isolé. Les frites foncées ne doivent pas être consommées, mais jetées à la poubelle. À l'exception de ces frites foncées, la qualité du produit est parfaitement en ordre et le produit peut être consommé. Nous dédommageons votre client pour le désagrément en émettant une note de crédit pour ce sac. Cordialement, Regine --------------- Original Message --------------- From: MONTAGNER Maurine [m.montagner@passionfroid.fr] Sent: 4/06/2024 09:04 To: Regine.Legein@agristo.com Subject: R32074 - 262853 Bonjour, Suite à une réclamation un client nous informe une anomalie sur la référence 26893 Frite bi temp 9/9 (2,5KGx4) /10KG PPF En effet, le client nous informe d’une quantité importante de frites de couleur foncée. La traçabilité incriminée est : DLC : 07/03/2026 LOT : DC 0524 070 Avez-vous eu d’autres réclamations ? Quelles sont les causes de cette anomalie ? Quelles actions allez-vous mettre en place ? Notre client demande donc un avoir sur 1 colis. Nous attendons votre retour sous 48h afin d’apporter une réponse au client. Bonne journée, Cordialement, ______________________________________________ Maurine MONTAGNER Service Qualité & RSE Passion Froid Est 12, rue du bois Jacquot - 54670 - Millery m.montagner@passionfroid.fr www.passionfroid.fr
Subject: R32074 - 262853

TextBody: Goedemiddag Regine, Gisteren zijn hier geen speciale dingen gebeurd. Als ik kijk naar de laadtijd van deze vracht was deze binnen de tijd geladen geen lange wachttijden omwille van breuken of iets dergelijks. Als ik naar de foto’s kijk van de pallets, dan zie ik ook een echt heel erg scheve pallet staan. Zulke pallets laden wij hier niet. Pallets die zo scheef staan, die gaan wij ook niet laden.
