TextBody: Hello Rachel, Kathleen is currently enjoying some time off, but I wish to get back to you on the below. Thank you for sharing this information, based on the pictures we have received we could link the following production: - Lot : D07 24 075 1215 - Packaging day : 15th March 2024 - Packaging order: 2128600 Having looked at the picture we indeed see the traversal seal has not been sealed properly. We unfortunately know the problem. The sealing of the bags is effectuated by heat. This means it is very imporatnt that the correct temperature is being used to seal the bags. Too high temperature would mean that the bags would meld, too low temperature means that the bags aren't sealed enough. Our production engineers have been working on this and did write an improved instruction, in order to have the most optimal temperature for sealing, taking into account the thickness and density of the foil. Also during production, every hour the operatores have to check the seal of the bags. A bag is taken from the line and is checked if seals are properly closed. Registrations of these checks are noted in QC documents. Having checked this particular run, I could not see any irregularties noted. Given the speed of our packaging lines, it must have occured that some bags escaped our monitoring system, for which we wish to apologize. We noted you currently had a complaint about 5 bags. Please be sure to keep us informed if any furhter complatins would be reported. At your disposal for further questions, Michèle Vandenbroucke Technical Sales Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: rachel low [rachellow@benfoods.com] Sent: 3/06/2024 11:08 To: Kathleen.Samyn@agristo.com Cc: Beau.Declerck@agristo.com; paulfoo@benfoods.com Subject: Packaging sealing issue - Farmchef Rosti Hashbrown External: Verify the sender before clicking any link/attachment. Hi Kathleen We received notice from 1 of our retailers that the packaging for Farmchef Rosti Hashbrown are not sealed properly again. This is not the first incident, as we have faced this issue before with the sealing. The outlet reported 5 affected packs, and will do a check across for any other occurrence. We do not have the date/batch print info on the carton as it has been discarded. But please refer to the product image attached for the time stamp. Thanks! Thank you &
Subject: Packaging sealing issue - Farmchef Rosti Hashbrown

TextBody: Hi, we have well received the metal wire and tested it on our metal detector. It was rejected 9/12 times. After thoroughly reviewing the piece, we don't believe the piece is origined from our production site. We don't see any product residue on the FB There were not metal icidents during this run This is a magnetic metal piece, so we suspect this is iron. All our machinery is stainless steel and thus non magnetic. We believe the likelihood of this small piece coming from the field into our process and travelling all the way through to your bag is very low. Can this come from the equipement at the consumer's home, such as the fryer?
Subject: [Request for confirmation] Claim Report 392084 　[597:Agristo(ヘ゛ルキ゛ー)]

TextBody: Dear, We have well received your below notification about the presence of a piece of blue plastic in the hash browns. Based on the lotcode we have received, the following batch is concerned: Lot : D08 24 128 Order: 1302132767 Packed: 6th and 7th of May After reviewing the complaint pictures, we believe this seems to match the bristles of the brush in the peeling lines. These are small, soft, plastic threads, in blue colour. On the 7th May, during their quality check round, QC has been logged a damaged brush near the peeling line 2 around 17h. Peeling line 2 was used for the production of the Hash Browns on 6th May from 5h20 to 22h24, 1 day before the brush incident. Afterwards peeling line 1 has been used for further production on 7th May. During the production on May 6th, QC conducted three quality checks, none of which reported irregularities near the peeling line. There are multiple steps after the peeling line to remove foreign objects (such as salt bath, metal detection, optical sorters, cutting knives, etc.), and since no ejections were reported in the packaging department, no product was blocked due to the damaged brush. To date, we have not received any similar complaints from that period. Based on our investigation and our rigorous quality controls, we believe this to be an isolated incident. Given that the foreign object is blue and easily noticeable, and is soft and incapable of causing injuries, we confirm there is no food safety risk. We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience this may have caused. If you have any further concerns or questions, please do not hesitate to contact us. Michèle Vandenbroucke Technical Sales Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Supplier complaint responses [supplierresponses@brake.co.uk] Sent: 3/06/2024 18:26 To: claims@agristo.com Cc: supplierresponses@brake.co.uk; ivonne.goetsch@sysco.com Subject: Foreign body complaint REF: 27446474 Good afternoon, REFERENCE NUMBER: 27446474 We have received the following foreign body complaint and request an investigation is carried out so that we can communicate the results back to our customer. Please investigate and respond with your report via email to: Supplierresponses@brake.co.uk covering the questions below within 5 working days of the date of this Email. Date Complaint recorded 03/06/2024 Product Maestro Hash Browns Triangle 1x2.5kg Brakes Product code 136961 Best before or use by date 06/05/2025 Or 06/05/2026 (picture is not clear) Batch Code D08 24 128 14:51 Customer Complaint Details Customer has found plastic in hash browns Please note that the response must include, as a minimum, the following points :- 1. Possible sources of contamination. 2. Precautions taken to prevent contamination/ensure detection. 3. Where a batch/date code is provided, and where relevant to the foreign body described, were your foreign body prevention/detection systems working correctly on the production day in question. 4. If from the description of the complaint you believe the item may have originated from your site, please confirm any action taken as a result. 5. Confirm whether any similar complaints have been received from any of your customer base. If so, what actions you have taken as a result. Please quote the above reference number in any correspondence and reply by email to: Supplierresponses@brake.co.uk
Subject: Foreign body complaint REF: 27446474

TextBody: Dag Veerle, Dank u wel voor de regeling vorige week om de stukjes terug bij ons te krijgen. Hopelijk kunnen we ook nog de deeltjes bemachtigen van de tweede klacht die nu bij het FAVV ligt. Hebben jullie al bericht gekregen van de instantie? In tussentijd is er al onderzoek gedaan naar de deeltjes die we in ons bezit hebben. Dit zijn de details van het onderzoek: Deeltje ontvangen van 1 klacht op 11/06 (opgestuurd door Colruyt Haacht) Bevindingen bij onderzoek van de deeltjes: • Geen witte achterkant: vermoedelijk dus niet van premix/grondstof. • kleur is lichter dan het blauw van de transportband. • deeltjes zijn minder hard dan de plastiek van de blauwe schoppen Kleur is gelijkend op die van blauwe handschoenen. Hoewel de deeltjes zeer klein zijn (max 2mm) lijken ze ook ietwat elastisch. Momenteel kunnen we niet vastleggen hoe een handschoen in dergelijk kleine deeltjes zou kunnen ‘versnipperd’ worden in ons productieproces. Bovendien werden er geen deeltjes IN de puree maar aan de buitenkant van de puree, ter hoogte van de korst, teruggevonden. Voorlopig kunnen we er dus nog niet de vinger op leggen waarvan de deeltjes afkomstig zijn. We weten nog niet zeker of er een verband is tussen de twee klachten, daar het andere deeltje vermoedelijk nog bij het FAVV zit. Ik heb al de details van onze onderzoeken in een document gegoten als overzicht voor u. Had u graag nog een meeting gehad met ons om het onderzoek nog eens te overlopen? Met vriendelijke groeten Sandrine Van Bockstael Technical Sales Officer Agristo nv P +32 498 60 12 06 --------------- Original Message ---------------
Subject: CMPL0047441 - Klacht - ART 22160 BONI aardappelkroketten oven 1kg
AGR_Extra_Information_Root_Cause__c: stukjes gekregen - lijkt het meest op handschoenen- tweede deel van onderzoek te vinden in klacht 00032193

TextBody: Bonjour, En annexe vous trouverez la note de crédit correspondant à cette plainte. Cordialement, Zoë Zoë Feys Customer Service Agristo nv P +32 56 54 11 67 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Agristo Claims [claims@agristo.com] Sent: 5/06/2024 11:31 To: m.montagner@passionfroid.fr Cc: Regine.Legein@agristo.com Subject: RE: R32074 - 262853 Bonjour, Nous avons bien reçu votre e-mail et l'avons enregistré sous le numéro de dossier 00029451. Nous regrettons que votre client ne soit pas satisfait de ce produit. Nous n'avons reçu aucune autre plainte à ce sujet. Les rapports de qualité horaires ne mentionnaient pas non plus de frites foncées. Après que les pommes de terre sont coupées en frites, elles sont brièvement blanchies, puis séchées, et pré-frites pendant environ 30 secondes à 180°C. Ces frites foncées ont probablement exceptionnellement passé le filtre du four de cuisson et ont été embarquées dans le four. L'huile dans le four de cuisson est continuellement filtrée, et sur la base des rapports du four de cuisson et des rapports de qualité horaires, nous sommes convaincus qu'il s'agit d'un incident isolé. Les frites foncées ne doivent pas être consommées, mais jetées à la poubelle. À l'exception de ces frites foncées, la qualité du produit est parfaitement en ordre et le produit peut être consommé. Nous dédommageons votre client pour le désagrément en émettant une note de crédit pour ce sac. Bonne journée, Cordialement, ______________________________________________ Maurine MONTAGNER Service Qualité & RSE Passion Froid Est 12, rue du bois Jacquot - 54670 - Millery m.montagner@passionfroid.fr www.passionfroid.fr

TextBody: EDEKA Kunden- und Ernährungsservice GUT&GÜNSTIG Backofen-Rösti-Ecken Issue Number: 2003588396 URGENT! Dear sir or madam we received the following customer’s complaint through our customer service. We expect you to review the incident immediately and send a first detailed statement within two hours after receiving this mail. Please see below for the reason for complaint and product details. Product: GTIN: 4311501057445 Article: Backofen-Rösti-Ecken Brand: GUT&GÜNSTIG BBD: 27.4.2026 Lot: D07 24 119 14:58 Issue: original text: Guten Tag, beim Essen der G&G Backofen Rösti-Ecken habe ich auf ein nicht identifizierbares festes, scharfkantiges Stück gebissen, was sehr weh getan hat. Ein kleines Stück, was davon abgebrochen ist, habe ich leider verschluckt. Im Anhang erhalten Sie Bilder vom besagten Stück (auch mit Größenvergleich) und die Verpackung der Rösti-Ecken. Hello, Whilst eating the G&G oven rosti wedges, I bit on an unidentifiable, firm, sharp-edged piece, which really hurt. Unfortunately, I swallowed a small piece that broke off. TextBody: Dear Reklamation, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00029982. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : D07241191458 Packaging day : 28/04/2024 The production process includes numerous physical and optical elimination steps to detect and remove foreign objects. Agristo continuously strives to invest in the latest best practice technical solutions to prevent foreign object contamination. Initially, the potatoes go through a stone remover, which operates based on centrifugal forces and effectively eliminates any objects heavier than potatoes. Following the stone remover, there is a water bath to remove floating particles, and a hedgehog conveyor that eliminates leafage. The leafage adheres to the pins that extend from the conveyor and is subsequently removed. After peeling and washing, the potatoes undergo optical sorting to eliminate foreign objects. Using a color camera, a mechanical system rejects foreign bodies, green potatoes, and potatoes with severe defects and diseases. The potatoes are then transported to the production line, where they are cut and inspected for black parts by a second optical sorter, and any defects are rejected using compressed air. Additionally, small dark-colored foreign bodies are detected and rejected. These initial steps are designed to effectively remove foreign bodies from the potatoes. Unfortunately, it appears that in this instance, a foreign body has managed to evade these steps. However, based on the provided picture and description, we are unable to determine the root cause of this issue. Could you please send this foreign object to the address provided below for further investigation? Agristo nv (for Ines Aerts) Venecoweg 12 9810 Nazareth We have checked our quality records for this run and we noticed nothing in particular for now. We do apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.

TextBody: Beste, Wij mochten onderstaande consumentenklacht met betrekking tot de textuur van de G'woon ovenfriet 1000g in goede orde ontvangen. Het spijt ons te vernemen dat uw consument een negatieve ervaring had met een door Agristo geproduceerd artikel. Wij hechten immers het grootste belang aan de kwaliteit van onze producten en verpakkingen. Wij hebben deze melding in ons systeem geregistreerd onder ticket 29987. Aan de hand van de lotcode (B01240441219 ) en de vervaldatum (12/02/2026) hebben wij kunnen achterhalen dat dit een productie betreft van 13/02/2024. We hebben de productiebladen en de kwaliteitscontroles van deze batch gecontroleerd – er werden geen anomalieën genoteerd. De volledige productie was conform. De tijden die op de verpakking staat zijn gevalideerd in gekalibreerde oven door onze kwaliteitsdienst. Elke oven is verschillend en kan afwijken van temperatuur. Hierdoor is het mogelijk dat het product langer in de oven moet. Wij hebben geen eerdere klachten hieromtrent ontvangen en gaan ervanuit dat dit een geïsoleerd geval is. Alvast bedankt om ons hiervan op de hoogte te brengen. TextBody: Sehr geehrte Herr Leuchten, Wir haben die folgende Verbraucherbeschwerde über einen Fremdkörper in den Bofrost BIO Katoffelkeilen in gutem Zustand erhalten. Es tut uns leid zu erfahren, dass Ihr Verbraucher eine negative Erfahrung mit einem von Agristo hergestellten Artikel gemacht hat. Schließlich legen wir größten Wert auf die Qualität unserer Produkte und Verpackungen. Wir haben diese Meldung in unserem System unter dem Ticket 27709 registriert. Anhand des Chargencodes (A04 23 270 2145 ) und des Verfallsdatums (26.09.2025) konnten wir herausfinden, dass es sich um eine Produktion vom 27.09.2023 handelt. Wir überprüften die Produktionsblätter und Qualitätskontrollen dieser Charge - es wurden keine Anomalien festgestellt. Die gesamte Produktion war vorschriftsmäßig. Bevor die Kartoffeln als Keile in Beutel verpackt werden, durchlaufen sie einen umfangreichen Prozess, um Fremdkörper zu erkennen: Der Produktionsprozess umfasst viele physische und optische Schritte zur Eliminierung von Fremdkörpern. Agristo versucht auch, in alle neuen technischen Lösungen zur Vermeidung von Fremdkörpern zu investieren. Wenn die Kartoffeln in unseren Betrieb kommen, wird das Metall zunächst mit einem Magneten entfernt. Dann durchlaufen die Kartoffeln einen Steinlöser. Der Steinentferner arbeitet mit Zentrifugalkräften und entfernt alle Gegenstände, die schwerer sind als Kartoffeln. Nach dem Steinentferner durchlaufen sie ein Wasserbad, um alle schwimmenden Teile zu entfernen, und ein Igelband, um das Laub zu entfernen. Das Laub bleibt an den aus dem Band kommenden Stiften hängen und wird auf diese Weise entfernt. Nachdem die Kartoffeln geschält und gewaschen wurden, durchlaufen sie einen optischen Sortierer, um Fremdkörper zu entfernen. Durch eine Farbkamera werden Fremdkörper, grüne Kartoffeln und Kartoffeln mit schweren Mängeln und Krankheiten durch ein mechanisches System aussortiert. Die Kartoffeln werden dann in die Produktionslinie gepumpt, wo sie geschnitten und von einem zweiten optischen Sortierer auf schwarze Teile überprüft werden - die Fehler werden mit Druckluft entfernt. Kleine dunkel gefärbte Fremdkörper werden ebenfalls erkannt und aussortiert. Wir haben den Fremdkörper erhalten und ihn mit unserem Metalldetektor getestet (siehe Anhang). Das Stück ist eher ein sehr kleiner Stein, weshalb es vom Metalldetektor nicht ausgeworfen wird. Außerdem gehen wir davon aus, dass dieses Stück, da es sich in der Tasche befand, durch einen der verschiedenen Eliminierungsschritte entfernt werden wird. Wir vermuten daher, dass das Stück nicht von uns stammt. Mit freundlichen Grüßen, Evelien Cremers Evelien Technical Sales Officer Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: No-reply [noreply.salesforce@agristo.com] Sent: 27/05/2024 15:40 To: jeroen.perseyn@agristo.com; joke.vansteenkiste@agristo.com Subject: Further investigation requested for complaint 00027709 Dear, Further investigation was requested for complaint 00027709. Below you find relevant information of complaint. An investigator needs to be appointed. Overview Complaint: - Company name: BOFROST DIENSTLEISTUNGS GmbH & Co K - Reason for complaint: Foreign body -- Details for complaint: Metal -- Customer description: - Responsible party: Harelbeke (P010) - AH1 Request from CX: Deeltje metaal is ontvangen en zal met interne post naar jullie toekomen. Kunnen jullie kijken of dit wordt uitgestoten door onze metaal detectie. CX Owner: Evelien Cremers Link to complaint: 00027709 Thanks for taking up this further investigation.
Subject: Bofrost* Fremdteil in BIO Kartoffel wedges

TextBody: Hi Eileen, About the corrective actions; According to HACCP principles, the inkjet on the bag is checked at the start of each run and then every hour. These hourly checks cover what is produced in between as when a stamp is okay at 23h00 and at 00h00, there is no reason or possibility for a missing stamp between those hours. As all checks turned out okay during this run, we suspect that the bags with missing code should be from the end of the run. We will keep performing these checks as usual and will keep an extra eye open during the next production runs of this product.
Subject: Agristo / Cial / Technical claim: bags without inkjet

TextBody: Hi Eileen, About the corrective actions; According to HACCP principles, the inkjet on the bag is checked at the start of each run and then every hour. These hourly checks cover what is produced in between as when a stamp is okay at 23h00 and at 00h00, there is no reason or possibility for a missing stamp between those hours. As all checks turned out okay during this run, we suspect that the bags with missing code should be from the end of the run. We will keep performing these checks as usual and will keep an extra eye open during the next production runs of this product.
Subject: Agristo / Cial / Technical claim: bags without inkjet

TextBody: Good Afternoon I have today received the mentioned foreign object and I will forward this to you in today’s post. Thanks Terek Terek Hazell Farmfoods Limited Office: 0121 700 7160 From: Agristo Claims <claims@agristo.com> Sent: Thursday, June 6, 2024 12:47 PM To: Terek Hazell <thazell@farmfoods.co.uk> Cc: samanthamyrie87@live.com Subject: RE: Ref: 324042TH Customer Enquiry Dear Terek Hazell, Thank you for delivering us some more detailed information about this complaint. Based on this specific lotcode we were able to determin the exact production date, 10/05/2023. Furthermore, we were also able to do a more profound investigation based on the specific lotcode regarding production timing. I have checked the QC results around the hour of packing (14u16). We had an hourly check at 14:38; 15:14. I have checked the tasting information as well as the hourly analysis. There were no foreign bodies found and there were no remarks made regarding fat clumps or problems with the oven. We hope with this extra investigation we have reassured you that this would be an isolated case.
Subject: Ref: 324042TH Customer Enquiry

TextBody: Bonjour, J'ai demandé des informations sur cet envoi au service expédition. Ce chargement a été effectué à Agristo Wielsbeke le mardi 4 juin 2024. Aucun commentaire n'a été noté ce jour-là. Le camion a été chargé dans les temps (début du chargement 16h48 – fin du chargement 17h16) . Nous effectuons également un contrôle de température avec un thermomètre sur un pallet aléatoire par chargement, et cette valeur est enregistrée dans notre système de gestion du transport. Pour ce chargement, une valeur de -20°C a été notée. Veuillez trouver ci-dessous les rapports de chargement. Sur les photos que vous nous avez envoyées, nous constatons que les palettes sont empilées de manière très oblique. Les palettes ne sont pas chargées de cette manière chez nous. Nous nous demandons comment ces palettes sont arrivées dans cet état chez vous et si le chauffeur du camion a bien mis en marche la réfrigération. Cordialement, Regine
Subject: PPF OUEST:  URGENT - Anomalie produits - AGRISTO

TextBody: Dag Tania, Er waren voor Scamark meerdere klachten geregistreerd op D0324107 - artikel 310609 voor open lasnaden. -28010 -27923 -27816 -26925 -28005 Je had mij als antwoord gediend in case 28009: Echter, de tijden van de voorbeelden veranderen. Ik had dit dan ook zo gelaten. Echter klant is nu teruggekomen met de vraag tot uitgebreide analyse en een EXCEL met voorbeelden. Daarenboven vragen zij onderstaande: Zouden jullie hierin kunnen voorzien of voor mij ergens iets voorzien van preventieve/correctieve acties? 1°/ TRAÇABILITE - La traçabilité à envoyer sous format Excel : les centrales livrées (dont les plates-formes étrangères), les quantités livrées par centrale de destination avec les dates de livraison, n°SSCC palettes, numéro de commande client, numéro de lot et DLC/DLUO correspondantes. 2°/ ANALYSE DES CAUSES - La copie des contrôles réalisés en cours de conditionnement pour les lots en question. Est-ce que l’ensemble des lots est concerné par ce problème? - Vos analyses sur le produit fini concerné. Est-ce que votre échantillothèque présente ce défaut? Si oui, pourriez-vous nous envoyer des photos? - Votre interprétation quant à cette non-conformité et le risque résiduel que d’autres numéros de lots présentent cette problématique. 3°/ ACTION CORRECTIVE Suite à cette non-conformité, merci de nous indiquer les actions correctives mises en place pour éviter que ce type de non-conformité ne se renouvelle. TextBody: Dear, Thank you for informing us about the below complaint, which has been logged as our Ticket ID 302230 In the details of this complaint, we have noticed the lotcode is missing, so we have run our traceability based on the expiry date mentioned, 01-04-2025. A BBE date of April 2025, refers to production of April 2023, in which we had 2 productions on these Coated Roast Potatoes. * 23/04/2023: Order 1202112209 - Baking order 1030798 * 04/04/2023: Order 1202111592 - Baking order 1030705 I believe you are aware that we have a full Quality Assurence System in place, in which the product is thouroughly checked every hour. A part of these quality controls, is to monitor/check the black bits/defects present on the potatoes. The results of these checks are carefully noted in our QC registration document. Having checked the concerned batches in our system, we could see that both productions have been produced within the predefined specification. We indeed observe that at certain times we are at the upper limit of the specification, but still wihtin spec. Since no detailed lotcode is availlable, it is difficult to estimate whether this could be related. The presence of black spots may be related to the production period (April), as we are nearing the end of the season. Of course, we always strive for the best quality, but since we work with a natural product, some variation is inevitable. We do however apologize for the inconvenience. Hope this info serves you well. At your disposal for further quesitons, Michèle Vandenbroucke Technical Sales Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Jennifer Deduytschaver [jennifer.deduytschaver@agristo.com] Sent: 6/06/2024 13:23 To: Michele.Vandenbroucke@agristo.com Subject: FW: Bidfood Product Quality Complaint Letter ref 11911039 Dag Michèle Zou jij deze klacht kunnen behandelen? Alvast bedankt! Mvg, Jennifer Jennifer Deduytschaver Technical Sales Officer T +32 56 54 10 52 Ridder de Ghellinckstraat 9 • 8710 Wielsbeke • Belgium • www.agristo.com -----Oorspronkelijk bericht-----

TextBody: Hello Sharon Thank you for informing us about the below, we have promptly registered it in our system below case 30262. Corresponding batch information: Lotcode : G08 24 038 15:10 Production day : 07/02/2024 In all our production plants we have very stringent hygiene rules and measurements. All visitors, operators or working personnel have to wear hair nets and protective clothing. Also men with beards have to wear a beard net. We also have a procedure for how we have to put these on: first the hair and beard net have to be put on, afterwards the protective clothing, this is to avoid having hair on the protective clothing. It seems that despite our efforts to prevent hair to end up in the product this one must have escaped our procedures. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.

TextBody: Dear, Thank you for informing us about the below incident, which we have registered in our system as ticket ID 30311. Based on the lotcode, the following product is concerned: Lot G25241262009 Product Harvest Basket Skin On Fries 750g Production 05/05/2024 Batch: 2133831 Generally, we have the below action plan to eliminate metal pieces from our production process: To eliminate the presence of metal, there is a metal detector on each packaging line. This metal detector is placed after the product is packed. When metal is detected the product is rejected and falls into a closed box. The detected metal is carefully registered and analyzed. The cause and origin of the possible contamination is detected and the necessary actions are always taken The functioning of these metal detectors are tested each hour with test bars with sizes Ø2mm Fe, Ø 2mm Non Fe and Ø 3.5mm Stainless steel. There is a very detailed metal detection instruction in place and our packaging operators are trained each year. A bag is taken out of a box after the metal detector, to make sure that there is no metal in the bag. The Ø 2mm Fe test bar is glued with tape to the bag and put on the conveyor before the metal detector. When the bag is detected, this is repeated for Non Fe and Stainless steel. When the bag isn’t rejected, the packaging line is stopped and the packed products are blocked until the last positive control. These blocked bags are then rechecked on a good working metal detector. We have checked our production log from the concerned batch/date and could not find any remarks or breakdown, which could be related to this complaint. Also the metal detection records of this production of 5th May – Line 25 have been checked, and nothing abnormalities. You can find the log attached. The checks effecutated just before (green) and just after (yellow) the time of your complaint, have been marked. As you can see, no bags have been rejected and metal checks did function properly. We can already confirm not having received any similar complaints from this lot, or around the time of this production day. Based on our first investigation, at this point, we are therefore not able to determine the root cause of this incident. To investigate if this piece of metal would have come from our production line, it would be very useful if we could receive it for further investigation. To be sure it arrives correctly, please do send it to the following address and mention our reference number 30311 in your letter. Agristo NV Att. Michèle Vandenbroucke Ridder de Ghellinckstraat 9 8710 Wielsbeke Belgium After receiving, we can test the piece of metal over the concerned packaging line and see if they would have been detected. Should you have any other questions or concerns, please do not hesitate to contact me. In the meantime, our apologies for the inconvenience. Michèle Vandenbroucke Technical Sales Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message ---------------
Subject: Lidl GB Customer Complaint -  103326659 Please investigate

Het spijt ons te vernemen dat uw consument een negatieve ervaring had met een door Agristo geproduceerd artikel. Wij hechten immers het grootste belang aan de kwaliteit van onze producten en verpakkingen. Wij hebben deze melding in ons systeem geregistreerd onder ticket 30201. Aan de hand van de lotcode (G25240821608 ) en de vervaldatum (21/03/2026) hebben wij kunnen achterhalen dat dit een productie betreft van 22/03/2024 We hebben de productiebladen en de kwaliteitscontroles van deze batch gecontroleerd – er werden geen anomalieën genoteerd. De volledige productie was conform. Na het schillen van de aardappel, worden deze in verschillende groten verdeeld ( klein, middel, groot). Elke grote heeft zijn snijmes. Kleintjes worden in 6 partjes gesneden, middel en groot in 8 partjes. Na het snijden komen ze allemaal terug samen om zo verder het productie proces door te gaan. Het kan dus zeker dat er verschillende grote in een zak zitten, echter zullen de hele kleine stukjes voor de inpak eruit gesorteerd worden. Gezien wij nog geen verder klachten hierover gekregen hebben, vermoeden we dat het dikte verschil dat de klant heeft gevonden in de zak een uitzonderlijk geval zal zijn. Alvast bedankt om ons hiervan op de hoogte te brengen. Met vriendelijke groeten, Evelien Cremers Evelien Technical Sales Officer Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message ---------------
Subject: Klacht inzake BK - DV - Aardappelpartjes - zak 750g (inhoud 2023) -  (Kenmerk: 202405452-06) #ID-bX2NLH9K

TextBody: Dear Sarah Thank you for your email. I am concerned to hear about your recent purchase. We strive to ensure that all products supplied to us are of a standard and quality you would expect from Farmfoods. I have today forwarded your comments to the supplier of this product for them to look into further. In the meantime, please accept my sincere apologies for the inconvenience this must have caused. I would like to send you, with our compliments, a Farmfoods voucher as a gesture of goodwill. I would also like to enclose a self-addressed envelope for safe return of the mentioned object. Once received, I will forward this to the supplier to further aid their investigation. I will send this in today’s post to the address provided in your email. I do hope that you will continue to shop at Farmfoods as we do value your custom.
Subject: Ref: 324651JC Customer Enquiry

TextBody: Dear Marlies, Dear Melissa I am sorry to inform you that we could not give them an information of 1 carton we don’t know what is it, Toyota decided to destroy the 1 carton and proceed their import procedure as they need to clear the customs for delivering product to Kyoka shokuhin. We are required to take care of expenses for transportation and destruction of 1 carton. Thank you very much. Hagino From: Hagino - Japan Office <ax1@mopera.net> Sent: Thursday, June 6, 2024 10:23 PM To: 'Agristo Service' <service@agristo.com>; 'Melissa Samyn' <Melissa.Samyn@agristo.com> Subject: RE: TOYOTA REQUEST FOR CHECK ON 1CT NOT FOR TOYOTA WAS MIXED IN A CONTAINER Dear Marlies Good afternoon. If I am not mistaken I haven’t received the answer from you yet. Due to this 1 carton which we don’t know what it is, the Japan customs has suspend the import procedure of the container and Toyota is facing a problem. Can you please check and inform me what the product is ? Shoestring or Natural cut or something ? According to your answerer we are also required to modify current documents. I am sorry to ask you this request but it would be highly appreciated if you could come bac to me today, Thank you very much for your cooperation ! Hagino From: Hagino - Japan Office <ax1@mopera.net<mailto:ax1@mopera.net>> Sent: Thursday, June 6, 2024 1:00 AM To: 'Agristo Service' <service@agristo.com<mailto:service@agristo.com>> Subject: FW: TOYOTA REQUEST FOR CHECK ON 1CT NOT FOR TOYOTA WAS MIXED IN A CONTAINER Importance: High Dear Marlies I sent you following mail. I forgot to inform you important thing in my mail and I am sorry. But the customs suspend their customs clearance procedure of the whole container until we answer them what is 1 CT. So Is this possible to check and come back to me please ? Thank you very much for your help in advance. Hagino From: Hagino - Japan Office <ax1@mopera.net<mailto:ax1@mopera.net>> Sent: Wednesday, June 5, 2024 7:10 PM To: 'Agristo Service' <service@agristo.com<mailto:service@agristo.com>> Subject: TOYOTA REQUEST FOR CHECK ON 1CT NOT FOR TOYOTA WAS MIXED IN A CONTAINER Dear Marlies, In the following container there is 1CT which is not for Toyota was mixed in a pallet. Please have a look at attached photo. 5A/24 Destination Tokyo IV# 90593090 BL#MEDUAX570347 C/N#MEDU9094940 Toyota must to report to the customs what is this and destroy. Can you please advise what is the product ( shoestring / natural ) and destination where it should gone but actually came to Japan ? Thank you very much Hagino
Subject: TOYOTA REQUEST FOR CHECK ON 1CT NOT FOR TOYOTA WAS MIXED IN A CONTAINER

Cordialement, Alexis CAJDLER Chef de projets Emballages Frais et Surgelés Tel : 01 49 87 59 56 [Signature GPTW.jpg]<https://www.linkedin.com/company/scamark/> ---------- Forwarded message --------- De : Alexis CAJDLER <alexis.cajdler@scamark.leclerc> Date: lun. 3 juin 2024 à 18:06 Subject: Réclamations soudures sachets rosty 600g Pom'Lisse To: <service@agristo.com<mailto:service@agristo.com>> Cc: Marlies De Ketele <Marlies.DeKetele@agristo.com<mailto:Marlies.DeKetele@agristo.com>> Bonjour, Je vous contacte suite à la réception d'une réclamation emballage concernant la référence de Rosty 600g Pom'Lisse pour un problème de mauvaise soudure du sachet. Ci joint dans l'excel le détail des réclamations. Dans ce contexte, pourriez-vous me communiquer les éléments suivants : 1°/ TRAÇABILITE - La traçabilité à envoyer sous format Excel : les centrales livrées (dont les plates-formes étrangères), les quantités livrées par centrale de destination avec les dates de livraison, n°SSCC palettes, numéro de commande client, numéro de lot et DLC/DLUO correspondantes. 2°/ ANALYSE DES CAUSES - La copie des contrôles réalisés en cours de conditionnement pour les lots en question. Est-ce que l’ensemble des lots est concerné par ce problème? - Vos analyses sur le produit fini concerné. Est-ce que votre échantillothèque présente ce défaut? Si oui, pourriez-vous nous envoyer des photos? - Votre interprétation quant à cette non-conformité et le risque résiduel que d’autres numéros de lots présentent cette problématique. 3°/ ACTION CORRECTIVE Suite à cette non-conformité, merci de nous indiquer les actions correctives mises en place pour éviter que ce type de non-conformité ne se renouvelle. Merci par avance pour votre retour avant le 10/06. Belle journée à vous, Alexis CAJDLER Chef de projets Emballages Frais et Surgelés Tel : 01 49 87 59 56 [Signature GPTW.jpg]<https://www.linkedin.com/company/scamark/>

TextBody: Hi Hannah, Below an answer on your questions. You have answered only “No” to “Have you reviewed retained samples / taste panel records - any deviation to specification?” Please confirm did you review the retained samples? We did not revieuw the retained samples Have you received any other complaints for blue hard plastic recently? No, we did not receievd any other complaint the last year about hard bleu plastic Do you do any inspection on plastic pallet integrity if there is a possibility of loose pieces entering the bags? The condition of the pallets is checked upon receipt (not registered), but this check mainly takes into account deviations that could affect stability. Due to the low number of complaints, the way the process is structured and the fact that an operator operates this installation, the risk is assessed as low. Please attach glass and hard plastic checks, do these include pallet integrity? See annex - P-A-03-03 Glasincident Glascontroles dec 2022 Please send glass and hard plastic policies. See annex - P-A-09-02 Glasaudit Please send relevant production records. Please send relevant foreign body detection checks (optical sorts, visual inspection, x-ray) See annex _ controleformulier werking optische sorteerder Hope with this information we can close this case.

TextBody: Dear Emma, Thank you for your email. I am concerned to hear about your recent purchase. We strive to ensure that all products supplied to us are of a standard and quality you would expect from Farmfoods. I have today forwarded your comments to the supplier of this product for them to look into further. In the meantime, please accept my sincere apologies for the distress and inconvenience this must have caused. I would like to send you, with our compliments, a Farmfoods voucher as a gesture of goodwill. I would also like to enclose a self-addressed envelope for safe return of the mentioned object. Once received, I will forward this to the supplier to further aid their investigation. I will send this in today's post to the address provided in your email. I do hope that you will continue to shop at Farmfoods as we do value your custom.

Het betreft goederen SAP 429194 geladen op 20/02/24 te Agristo, Wielsbeke, Belgium 10 zak x 20kg Onze referenties : VE 12310268 – AN 12300268 Graag hiervoor jullie CN. Anbei nun die richtigen Frachtpapiere. Sorry für die Umstände. ** unquote ** Alvast bedankt. TextBody: Bonjour, Nous avons également discuté en détail de votre plainte avec nos départements de la chaîne d'approvisionnement et nous vous envoyons ainsi les commentaires suivants : Le transport est sous les incoterms FCA. Agristo est responsable du chargement des marchandises sur le véhicule désigné par le client. Une fois les marchandises chargées, les risques et les coûts de transport sont transférés au client. Le client est alors responsable du transport ultérieur des marchandises jusqu'à la destination finale, y compris les procédures douanières et les coûts éventuels. De telles palettes bancales ne peuvent pas être stockées dans notre entrepôt frigorifique. Il n'est donc pas possible qu'elles soient sorties de notre entrepôt de cette manière. Sur la photo 4, une température de -17,6°C est visible, mais il semble que ce soient des cartons imprimés. Vos marchandises pour la marque Bon & Engagé sont emballées par Agristo dans des cartons bruns neutres sans impression. La photo ne montre donc pas des marchandises produites par Agristo. En espérant vous avoir ainsi suffisamment informé, Cordialement, Régine --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Regine Legein [regine.legein@agristo.com] Sent: 6/06/2024 17:35 To: sophie.rondou@agristo.com; claims@agristo.com; a.cesaroni@passionfroid.fr Cc: dqse-alerte-alimentaire@groupe-pomona.fr; s.rapy@groupe-pomona.fr; a.kerdudou@passionfroid.fr Subject: RE: RECURRENCE : PPF OUEST: URGENT - Anomalie produits - AGRISTO Bonjour, J'ai demandé des informations sur cet envoi au service expédition. Ce chargement a été effectué à Agristo Wielsbeke le mardi 4 juin 2024. Aucun commentaire n'a été noté ce jour-là. Le camion a été chargé dans les temps (début du chargement 16h48 – fin du chargement 17h16) . Nous effectuons également un contrôle de température avec un thermomètre sur un pallet aléatoire par chargement, et cette valeur est enregistrée dans notre système de gestion du transport. Pour ce chargement, une valeur de -20°C a été notée. Veuillez trouver ci-dessous les rapports de chargement. Sur les photos que vous nous avez envoyées, nous constatons que les palettes sont empilées de manière très oblique. Les palettes ne sont pas chargées de cette manière chez nous. Nous nous demandons comment ces palettes sont arrivées dans cet état chez vous et si le chauffeur du camion a bien mis en marche la réfrigération. Cordialement, Regine Regine​​​​ Legein Technical Sales Officer T +32 56 54 11 57 • M +32 486 20 82 42 Ridder de Ghellinckstraat 9 • 8710 Wielsbeke • Belgium • www.agristo.com
Subject: PPF OUEST:  URGENT - Anomalie produits - AGRISTO

TextBody: Geachte, Bedankt dat u deze kwestie onder onze aandacht heeft gebracht. Wij hebben het direct in ons systeem geregistreerd onder ticketnummer 00030582. Het spijt ons te horen dat uw klant niet tevreden was over de kwaliteit van deze batch. De kwaliteit van onze producten is voor ons van het allergrootste belang en wij doen er alles aan om deze kwestie op te lossen. Graag had ik verwezen naar de klacht CMPL0045255 met dezelfde lotcode. Hierbij gaan wij vanuit dat deze klacht gerelateerd is tot hetzelfde probleem namelijk het slecht functioneren van onze mesbekken. De lotcodes van beide klachten verschillen slechts enkele minuten. Wij willen ons verontschuldigen voor het ongemak. Zou het mogelijk zijn om toekomstige klachten naar claims@agristo.com te sturen aub? Dit voor een vlotte behandeling van de dossiers. Mocht u verder vragen hebben, contacteer ons gerust. Met vriendelijke groeten Sandrine Van Bockstael Technical Sales Officer Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 ---------

TextBody: Dear Chloe Rutter, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00030602. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : D01241000035 Packaging day : 9/04/2024 The production process includes numerous physical and optical elimination steps to detect and remove foreign objects. Agristo continuously strives to invest in the latest best practice technical solutions to prevent foreign object contamination. Initially, the potatoes go through a stone remover, which operates based on centrifugal forces and effectively eliminates any objects heavier than potatoes. Following the stone remover, there is a water bath to remove floating particles, and a hedgehog conveyor that eliminates leafage. The leafage adheres to the pins that extend from the conveyor and is subsequently removed. After peeling and washing, the potatoes undergo optical sorting to eliminate foreign objects. Using a color camera, a mechanical system rejects foreign bodies, green potatoes, and potatoes with severe defects and diseases. The potatoes are then transported to the production line, where they are cut and inspected for black parts by a second optical sorter, and any defects are rejected using compressed air. Additionally, small dark-colored foreign bodies are detected and rejected. These initial steps are designed to effectively remove foreign bodies from the potatoes. Unfortunately, it appears that in this instance, a foreign body has managed to evade these steps. However, based on the provided picture and description, we are unable to determine the root cause of this issue. Could you please send this foreign object to the address provided below for further investigation? TAV Inez Aerts Venecoweg 12, 9810 Nazareth Belgium We do apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: Ref: 324697CR Customer Enquiry

TextBody: Dear Emma, Thank you for your email. I am concerned to hear about your recent purchase. We strive to ensure that all products supplied to us are of a standard and quality you would expect from Farmfoods. I have today forwarded your comments to the supplier of this product for them to look into further. In the meantime, please accept my sincere apologies for the distress and inconvenience this must have caused. I would like to send you, with our compliments, a Farmfoods voucher as a gesture of goodwill. I would also like to enclose a self-addressed envelope for safe return of the mentioned object. Once received, I will forward this to the supplier to further aid their investigation. I will send this in today’s post to the address provided in your email. I do hope that you will continue to shop at Farmfoods as we do value your custom.
Subject: Ref: 324697CR Customer Enquiry

TextBody: Hi Shani, OK. Let us know asap. Has something changed in the checks/controls as we keep on getting notifications of Listeria suspects? TextBody: Bonjour Nous nous questionnons aussi sur ce litige, * Le transport est sous les incoterms FCA. Agristo est responsable du chargement des marchandises sur le véhicule désigné par le client. Une fois les marchandises chargées, les risques et les coûts de transport sont transférés au client. Le client est alors responsable du transport ultérieur des marchandises jusqu'à la destination finale, y compris les procédures douanières et les coûts éventuels. => notre transporteur nous dit que vous l’obligez à couper le groupe froid de la semi pour le chargement. Sans cette action, vous refusez de charger Pourquoi ? * De telles palettes bancales ne peuvent pas être stockées dans notre entrepôt frigorifique. Il n'est donc pas possible qu'elles soient sorties de notre entrepôt de cette manière. => En cours d’échange avec le transporteur * Sur la photo 4, une température de -17,6°C est visible, mais il semble que ce soient des cartons imprimés. Vos marchandises pour la marque Bon & Engagé sont emballées par Agristo dans des cartons bruns neutres sans impression. La photo ne montre donc pas des marchandises produites par Agristo. => c’était pour vous montrer la prise de température acceptable, mais nous sommes bien informés que ce ne sont pas vos produits Merci pour votre retour Bien cordialement ______________________________________________ Axelle CESARONI Adjointe à la Responsable Qualité Sécurité Environnement Qualité Sécurité Environnement PASSIONFROID OUEST

TextBody: Bonjour Carole, Cette plainte, n'est-il pas exactement la même comme NCI-24/25 COMPL_9273_2024-04-18? En ce qui concerne la soudure: Avec le n° du lot nous ne pouvons pas retrouver l'heure de production. Je tiens à vous assurer que lors du processus d'emballage, nous effectuons des contrôles de qualité. Notre équipe teste les fermetures des sacs toutes les heures. Un carton est retiré de la ligne d’emballage, et tous les sacs sont minutieusement inspectés pour garantir que les emballages sont correctement fermés. Les résultats de ces inspections sont consignés dans nos documents de qualité. Nous ne voyons aucune déviation pendant cette production. Nous ne pouvons pas lier cette plainte à une changement de film. En ce qui concerne la forme: Nous avons vérifié les rapports de production; - Liste d'actions : aucun rapport le 17/12 concernant la forme. - Temps d'arrêt : aucun temps d'arrêt n'a été enregistré - Mesure 16h44 du diamètre le 17/12 : écarts mineurs sur un échantillon de 10 pièces : moins 31,01 mm alors que la limite minimale est de 32 mm. Cependant, la qualité a été évaluée comme OKE à ce moment-là sur la base du livre de photos (où la différence de taille est considérée comme défectueuse et devrait être de 10% maximum). Le poids moyen (10 pièces) à ce moment-là était de 14,21 g, donc parfaitement dans la norme (13-17 g). Le contrôle a également été satisfaisant. D'après la photo, nous décrivons cette vue comme un UFO. Une fiche EHBP distincte est disponible à cet effet (premiers soins en cas de problèmes). Dans la plupart des cas, cela s'explique par le fait que la machine de formage n'est pas entièrement remplie, ce qui entraîne brièvement des différences de pression et donc des formes irrégulières. Il incombe à l'opérateur sur la ligne de surveiller attentivement ce point pendant le processus. Étant donné que les contrôles de qualité horaires ne révèlent aucun écart majeur, le responsable qualité soupçonne qu'il s'agit ici d'un problème momentané lié à la vidange des machines. Cordialement, Hanne Hanne Verstaen Technical Sales Officer P +32 56 54 10 60 --------------- Original Message ---------------
Subject: Non Conformité NCI-24/30 - COMPL_9272_2024-04-18

TextBody: Dear James Curran , Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00030729. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Bath information: Lotcode : B02241200256 Production day : 29/04/2024 There is a complete Quality Assurance system in place and the principles of HACCP are applied. This includes a full monitoring system on the production line. The finished products themselves are sampled every 60 minutes and examined for quality, including length and slivers. Full records of these and all the other checks are maintained. Based on the lotcode, we have conducted a thorough investigation into our production records and quality documents for this specific batch. There were no remarks or abnormalities registered during this run regarding the length or broken pieces. It's important to note that there will always be variations in production throughout the year due to the inherent nature of potatoes as a natural product. From a technical standpoint, we always strive to offer you the best possible product. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: Ref: 324752JC Customer Complaint

TextBody: Good morning, we wish to reach out to you as we have received your writing included with the actual FB. Unfortunately, we have to acknowledge that the item has been in transit for too long and has arrived in a moldy condition. Therefore, we are unable to conduct further investigation into what the possible contamination might have been. We would like to confirm that we have not received any similar complaints and thus believe this to be an isolated case. Nevertheless, we wish to apologize for this occurrence. At your disposal, Michèle Vandenbroucke Technical Sales Agristo nv P +32 56 54 09 44 --------------- Original Message ---------------

TextBody: Bonjour, Oui, c'est correct. Nous faisons cela afin d'assurer des conditions de travail acceptables pour nos caristes, afin qu'ils ne soient pas continuellement exposés à un courant d'air glacé. Une fois le chargement terminé, le refroidissement peut être remis en marche. Le chauffeur peut, s'il le souhaite, être présent pendant le chargement à tout moment. TextBody: Beste Randa, Ik moet van mijn vorige mail nog iets verduidelijken: er wordt wel elk uur afgebakken om de kleur (Agtron) te meten. Deze waardes hebben geen sterke afwijking vertoond rondom het moment van de klacht. Er wordt niet van elk uur een tasting staal afgebakken, dit gebeurt steekproefsgewijs. Ondertussen werden de retentiestalen opgevraagd en gisteren beoordeeld. 10-06: Retentiestalen met lotcodes C01 24 076 1503 en C02 24 076 1555 afgebakken op 175°C gedurende zowel 3 als 4 minuten (zie bijgevoegde afbeeldingen). Bij beoordeling hiervan werd opgemerkt dat het product juist knapperig, egaal van kleur en binnen de lengte normen valt. Hier werden geen afwijkingen van de norm geconstateerd. Het beeld van de klant komt dan ook niet overeen met de afbak van de retentiestalen. De retentiestalen zijn knapperig, egaal en licht van kleur na afbak volgens instructies. Is het eventueel mogelijk dat de klant de afbakinstructies niet gevolgd heeft? Mvg, Regine --------------- Original Message ---------------

TextBody: Dear Pieter san, I'm sorry. I would like to ask you again about the issue of HASH BROWN ROUND being packaged together with BEAR SMILE POTATOES. The number of complaints I reported to you last time was three. However, we have received similar complaints from other customers since then. As of now, we have received a total of six complaints. The lots that we have been able to confirm are listed below. ①D01 23 181 15:17 ②D01 23 181 :15 ③D01 23 181 15:15 ④D01 23 181 15:14 Some of the questions are similar to the ones you answered previously but since there is a high possibility that the number of complaints will increase, I would like you to answer the following questions again. ・Is EXP2025.6.29 the only BEAR SMILE POTATOES that may have been contaminated with HASH BROWN ROUND? ・I understand that an operator mistakenly put HASH BROWN ROUND into line D01, where BEAR SMILE POTATOES were being packaged. Do you know when the operator did this? ex: Worked between 〇:〇 ~ △:△ ・We have BEAR SMILE POTATOES with the following expiration dates in our warehouse. From: Agristo Claims <claims@agristo.com<mailto:claims@agristo.com>> Sent: Tuesday, June 4, 2024 12:40 PM To: Daniel Taylor <daniel.taylor@fullersfoods.com<mailto:daniel.taylor@fullersfoods.com>> Cc: Melissa Watson <melissa.watson@fullersfoods.com<mailto:melissa.watson@fullersfoods.com>>; Alice Toop <alice.toop@fullersfoods.com<mailto:alice.toop@fullersfoods.com>>; Bethany Hopkin <bethany.hopkin@fullersfoods.com<mailto:bethany.hopkin@fullersfoods.com>> Subject: RE: FW: Asda Crinkle Cut Chips - Nutrition Out of Spec *** Please note the message below originated on the Internet. Please use caution when replying or opening links or attachments. *** Hi Dan, just for your info I want to share with you something we already shared on the NMR method 2 years ago: "Our experience over the last few years show the NMR method does not give a reliable result. It was always a method used commonly with milk powder which is a more homogeneous product but over the past few years appears to have been rolled out across other products such as our frozen potato products and is now commonly used in the UK. In fact we’ve had this exact same experience with another customer who was finding our products when tested weren’t in line with the nutrition in the spec/on pack. In this situation the results were as follows: - - Customer testing (NMR) = 4.9 - Spec/on pack claim = 9.7 - Same sample retested by customers lab but using Soxhlet method = 9.8 NB. For your interest I have attached a leaflet on NMR that does show results can come out lower but deemed to be not significant enough to worry about. Unfortunately we do not find this to be the case with our products. It also discusses how it is a preferred method as doesn’t require qualified staff and is a quicker method thus making it a much cheaper option, which explains a labs preference for using it." On potatoes: The variation depends on where we are in the season (early harvest, main harvest), as well as which potato variety is being used at that time. Since we work with natural products, it is not unusual to have natural variations in our products. Hopefully, the customer understands this as well. Of course, it is more meaningful to look at the overall picture and check the average from multiple analyses, rather than relying on just one analysis. Hope this helps!
Subject: FW: Asda Crinkle Cut Chips - Nutrition Out of Spec

From: Agristo Claims <claims@agristo.com> Sent: Tuesday, June 4, 2024 12:40 PM To: Daniel Taylor <daniel.taylor@fullersfoods.com> Cc: Melissa Watson <melissa.watson@fullersfoods.com>; Alice Toop <alice.toop@fullersfoods.com>; Bethany Hopkin <bethany.hopkin@fullersfoods.com> Subject: RE: FW: Asda Crinkle Cut Chips - Nutrition Out of Spec *** Please note the message below originated on the Internet. Please use caution when replying or opening links or attachments. *** Hi Dan, just for your info I want to share with you something we already shared on the NMR method 2 years ago: "Our experience over the last few years show the NMR method does not give a reliable result. It was always a method used commonly with milk powder which is a more homogeneous product but over the past few years appears to have been rolled out across other products such as our frozen potato products and is now commonly used in the UK. In fact we’ve had this exact same experience with another customer who was finding our products when tested weren’t in line with the nutrition in the spec/on pack. In this situation the results were as follows: - - Customer testing (NMR) = 4.9 - Spec/on pack claim = 9.7 - Same sample retested by customers lab but using Soxhlet method = 9.8 NB. For your interest I have attached a leaflet on NMR that does show results can come out lower but deemed to be not significant enough to worry about. Unfortunately we do not find this to be the case with our products. It also discusses how it is a preferred method as doesn’t require qualified staff and is a quicker method thus making it a much cheaper option, which explains a labs preference for using it." On potatoes: The variation depends on where we are in the season (early harvest, main harvest), as well as which potato variety is being used at that time. Since we work with natural products, it is not unusual to have natural variations in our products. Hopefully, the customer understands this as well. Of course, it is more meaningful to look at the overall picture and check the average from multiple analyses, rather than relying on just one analysis. Hope this helps!
Subject: FW: Asda Crinkle Cut Chips - Nutrition Out of Spec

TextBody: Hi Sharon Thank you for sharing the issue reported here below regarding a piece of plastic that was found in a bag of Green Isle Chunky chips. Batch information: Lotcode : B03 24 054 16:05 Production day : 23/02/2024 Best Before: 22/02/2026 The production process includes numerous physical and optical elimination steps to detect and remove foreign objects. Agristo continuously strives to invest in the latest best practice technical solutions to prevent foreign object contamination. Initially, the potatoes go through a stone remover, which operates based on centrifugal forces and effectively eliminates any objects heavier than potatoes. Following the stone remover, there is a water bath to remove floating particles, and a hedgehog conveyor that eliminates leafage. The leafage adheres to the pins that extend from the conveyor and is subsequently removed. After peeling and washing, the potatoes undergo optical sorting to eliminate foreign objects. Using a color camera, a mechanical system rejects foreign bodies, green potatoes, and potatoes with severe defects and diseases. The potatoes are then transported to the production line, where they are cut and inspected for black parts by a second optical sorter, and any defects are rejected using compressed air. Additionally, small dark-colored foreign bodies are detected and rejected. Based on the picture I received it seems indeed like a piece of melted plastic. Would you know when the customer noticed the piece of plastic? Was it before or after the product was cooked? At this point I assume that it may possible that a piece of the packaging was teared off when opening the bag and ended up together with the product being heated in the fryer or oven and causing is to melt. As this is an assumption only, would you be able to send this foreign body to the address here below in order to perform a further investigation? Agristo Tilburg FAO Quality department – case 30875 Heieinde 1 5047 SX Tilburg The Netherlands In the meantime I remain at your disposal in case of any other questions.
Subject: FW: [External] - Plastic object

TextBody: Hi Mania, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00030398. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Based on the provided pictures we have received, we can confirm this is a piece of sprout on the potato. Sprout can occur while the potatoes are being stored. Potatoes with sprout are still good for consumption, but the sprout should be removed. After frying , the sprout can indeed be very hard, like a piece of wood. It appears that, despite our best efforts, some foreign material may have escaped our monitoring systems. We are confident that this complaint is not widespread. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: FW: בנוגע לבקשת שירות #321,141 טופס מותג פרטי

TextBody: Bonjour, Nous avons bien reçu votre notification ci-dessous, qui a été enregistrée sous la reference 30908 Sur la bas du code lot, nous confirmerons que les frites ont été produits le 15 décembre 2023. * Lot: G 23 349 14h50 * Batch: 1033424 * Date: 15/12/2023 Tout d’abord, je voudrais vous informer que nous avons un système d’assurance qualité en place, dans lequel le produit final est soumis à un contrôle approfondi toutes les heures. Lors de ces contrôles, le nombre de défauts est également mesuré. Pour m’assurer que nous nous comrenons, j'aimerais savoir comment vous enregistrez les défauts ? Dans nos contrôles, les défauts sont comptés par nombre/1000g. Les valeurs dont vous parlez s'écartent également légèrement de nos valeurs prédéterminées. Veuillez voir nos commentaires dans le document ci-joint. En examinant les contrôles en détail, nous constatons qu'ils sont conformes à la spécification, mais qu'ils tendent parfois vers la limite. À titre d'action, nous avons déjà extrait des échantillons de rétention du code de lot en question à des fins de vérification. Comme vous pouvez le voir sur la photo ci-jointe, ils ne présentent pas de défauts excessifs. Bien entendu, nous nous efforçons toujours d'éliminer le plus de défauts possible de notre processus de production et d'ajuster les trieurs optiques avec précision. Cependant, nous travaillons avec un produit naturel, et nous nous efforçons toujours d'obtenir la meilleure qualité possible. Nous espérons pouvoir vous aider et restons à votre disposition pour toute question supplémentaire. TextBody: Cher/Chère Edouard Cailette, Nous vous remercions de nous avoir informé de ce sujet, que nous avons immédiatement enregistré dans notre système sous le numéro de ticket 00030263. Nous sommes désolés d'apprendre que votre client n'était pas satisfait de la qualité de cette série. La qualité de nos produits est d'une importance capitale pour nous, et nous sommes déterminés à résoudre cette question. Informations sur le batch: Code de lot : D05241212138 Jour d'emballage : 8/01/2024 Je tiens à vous assurer que lors du processus d'emballage, nous effectuons des contrôles de qualité. Notre équipe teste les fermetures des sacs toutes les heures. Un carton est retiré de la ligne d’emballage, et tous les sacs sont minutieusement inspectés pour garantir que les emballages sont correctement fermés. Les résultats de ces inspections sont consignés dans nos documents de qualité. Conformément aux préoccupations que vous avez soulevées, nous avons mené une enquête sur les contrôles d'emballage de cette série en particulier. Une note de crédit sera prévue. Nous regrettons tout désagrément que cette situation a pu causer à vous ou à votre client. Nous prenons cette question au sérieux et nous nous engageons à prévenir tels incidents à l'avenir. Si vous avez besoin de plus d'informations ou d'assistance supplémentaire, n'hésitez pas à nous contacter.

TextBody: Hello Elynn, Unfortunately, we can not propose this to the customer, this is not the correct way to deal with it. All taxes are calculated with the Invoice amount basis. So they would pay more taxes than they should pay. To solve this we have 2 options, amend the Invoice to the correct amount, or to give a dredit note with the price difference + the taxes difference, so this would not affect the final cost of the product. The most pratical and easy fro everybody would be to amend the Invoice to the correct price. Thank you, [cid:image003.jpg@01DABBED.E3244820] De: DELTA <delta@jaoliveira.com.br> Enviada em: terça-feira, 11 de junho de 2024 09:54 Para: 'Agristo Claims' <claims@agristo.com>; flv@jaoliveira.com.br; cacilda.jaoliveira@gmail.com Cc: bram.tuytens@agristo.com Assunto: RES: RES: FW: RES: Copacol / 00416/24 00201/24 / Docuemnts Hi Elynn, Thank you! @flv@jaoliveira.com.br<mailto:flv@jaoliveira.com.br> @cacilda.jaoliveira@gmail.com<mailto:cacilda.jaoliveira@gmail.com> Can you please check?

TextBody: Let op!: U kunt niet middels reply (Re) op deze e-mail reageren. Klik op de onderstaande link om te reageren. Beste leverancier, Wij ontvingen een melding over een PLUS product dat door u wordt geproduceerd. Om onze klant van een volledig antwoord te kunnen voorzien, hebben wij uw input nodig. Indien er geen monsters en/of codes in het dossier staan, zijn deze helaas niet (meer) beschikbaar. Omschrijving van ons verzoek: Beste, Wij ontvingen een klacht over onderstaande PLUS product dat door u wordt geproduceerd. PLUS Aardappelpartjes Zakje 750 GR Kort samengevat is de klacht als volgt: De aardappelpartjes bevatte een steen, lijkt op een lavasteen De volledige artikelgegevens, zoals de EAN-code, productiecode en THT (indien van toepassing) zijn beschikbaar via onderstaande link. Graag vernemen wij de mogelijke oorzaak en de wijze van kwaliteitscontrole van het product. Wij verzoeken u om uw reactie zo snel mogelijk doch, uiterlijk binnen 3 werkdagen door te geven middels de onderstaande link in deze e-mail. Indien langer onderzoek noodzakelijk is, ontvangen we graag de inmiddels genomen acties en controles binnen uw bedrijf. Indien er geen monsters en/of codes aanwezig zijn, zijn deze helaas niet (meer) beschikbaar. Mocht u meer tijd nodig hebben, wilt u ons dan zo snel mogelijk informeren? Deze klacht wordt door ons naar de consument afgehandeld en wij verzoeken u dan ook geen rechtstreeks contact met de consument op te nemen, tenzij na overleg met ons. TextBody: Dear James Curran , Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00030384. Bath information: Lotcode : G22240601650 Production day : 29/02/2024 In all our production plants we have very stringent hygiene rules and measurements. All visitors, operators or working personnel have to wear hair nets and protective clothing. Also men with beards have to wear a beard net. We also have a procedure for how we have to put these on: first the hair and beard net have to be put on, afterwards the protective clothing, this is to avoid having hair on the protective clothing We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.

TextBody: Beste lezer, Op het verzoek van PLUS Consumentenservice met referentienummer 240531-000388 heeft u zojuist de volgende reactie verstuurd: 12/6/2024 11:00 - Evelien Cremers Beste, Wij mochten onderstaande consumentenklacht met betrekking het vinden van een vreemd voorwerp in de PLUS Aardappelpartjes in goede orde ontvangen. Het spijt ons te vernemen dat uw consument een negatieve ervaring had met een door Agristo geproduceerd artikel. Wij hechten immers het grootste belang aan de kwaliteit van onze producten en verpakkingen. Wij hebben deze melding in ons systeem geregistreerd onder ticket 31018. Aan de hand van de lotcode ( G0924127 17:45) en de vervaldatum (05/05/2026) hebben wij kunnen achterhalen dat dit een productie betreft van 06/05/2024. We hebben de productiebladen en de kwaliteitscontroles van deze batch gecontroleerd – er werden geen anomalieën genoteerd. De volledige productie was conform. Het productieproces bevat veel fysieke en optische eliminatiestappen voor vreemde voorwerpen. Agristo probeert ook te investeren in alle nieuwe best practice technische oplossingen om vreemde voorwerpen te vermijden. Bij het binnenkomen van de aardappelen in ons bedrijf, wordt eerst het metaal verwijderd door middel van een magneet. Daarna gaan de aardappelen door een steensteenverwijderaar. De steenverwijderaar werkt op middelpuntvliedende krachten en verwijdert alle voorwerpen die zwaarder zijn dan aardappelen. Na de steenverwijderaar gaan ze door een waterbad om alle drijvende delen te verwijderen en door een egelband om het loof te verwijderen. Het loof plakt aan de pinnen die uit de band komen en wordt op die manier verwijderd. Nadat de aardappelen zijn geschild en gewassen, gaan ze door een optische sorteerder om vreemde voorwerpen te verwijderen. Door middel van een kleurencamera worden vreemde voorwerpen, groene aardappelen en aardappelen met zware gebreken en ziekten door een mechanisch systeem afgestoten. Daarna worden de aardappelen naar de productielijn gepompt waar ze worden versneden en door een tweede optische sorteerder worden gecontroleerd op zwarte delen - de defecten worden met perslucht verwijderd. Ook kleine donkergekleurde vreemde lichamen worden gedetecteerd en afgewezen. Daar u spreekt van een soort lava steen zou ik vermoeden dat het gaat om een vetklomp die is losgekomen uit de bakoven. Mocht u ons kunnen voorzien van een foto of het vreemde voorwerp kunnen opsturen kunnen wij dit beter onderzoeken wat de mogelijke oorzaak zou kunnen zijn. Alvast onze oprechte excuses voor dit voorval. Met vriendelijke groet, Evelien Cremers Uw antwoord zal, indien van toepassing, door PLUS Consumentenservice worden gebruikt om een antwoord richting de klant te formuleren. Mocht u nog vragen of opmerkingen hebben, neem dan gerust contact op met ons via 0800-222 44 43. Met vriendelijke groet, PLUS Consumentenservice
Subject: Melding PLUS Consumentenservice - 240531-000388 - Aardappelpartjes Zakje PLUS bevatte een steen, lijkt op lavasteen

TextBody: Dear Supplier, Please see details below of a customer complaint received by Iceland. A SAE has been sent to customer to return the Foreign Body and Packaging. The Foreign Body will be sent to you when Iceland receives it. Please start an initial investigation in the interim and send all reports and documents to sgsashby.icelandcomms@sgs.com <mailto:sgsashby.icelandcomms@sgs.com> The customer has provided photographs of the material which are attached. Please provide ALL the below – 1. Full investigation report, detailing how your full investigation was carried out and your findings with supporting documents, as attachment 2. In addition - Please answer the key points below in the table – The below should NOT be used as your full investigation report, it is a key points table in addition of you investigation report IMPORTANT: Iceland requires ALL Glass complaints to have external analysis carried out Product Name: CREAMY CHEESE & POTATO GRATIN Product Codes: PLU 58316 Best Before or Use By date: 12/02/2026 Batch Code/Lot code: D13 24 045 07:39 A Summary of complaint: Piece of hard white plastic wound inside the gratin Key points– if included in full investigation report; add comment ‘included in report’ Supplier Comments How many packs were produced? Line number Date of production Were any issues or non-conformances recorded for this production; including foreign body controls and monitoring equipment? Please outline the controls in place to prevent foreign material entering products Have you reviewed retained samples / taste panel records - any deviation to specification? Are complaints recorded and monitored for Trending purposes? How are complaints communicated to Staff / Senior Team? Could the root cause be identified? Outline Corrective Actions Provide copies as attachment to support investigation of any relevant records (as below- not limited too) * Glass & Plastic Checks * Production Records * Foreign body detection checks (Metal detector, X-Ray, Filters, optical sorts) * QC Checks * Taste Panel /Retained Samples * External Independent Laboratory Analysis Report – Iceland requirement for ALL glass complaints Please note that any documents that are not in English – Key Points will be required to be translated (this can be handwritten onto the document for ease). Please confirm receipt of the complaint and provide a response within 48 hours. If you have any issues or queries, please do not hesitate to contact me. Please ensure you complete all sections of the blue table that are blank, attach all relevant documents together with a final report, otherwise it will be rejected back to you for completion.
Subject: Iceland Customer Product Complaint 03369820

TextBody: Dear Jack Lo, We are very sorry to hear you have reason to complaint. Based on the given lot code D05 24 043 1643, I could trace back production date and I could check our quality and production records. According to our QC log files and production files, there were no issues reported. The colour was within spec and we did not struggle with broken product. We check the product after it has been packed in bags. If a lot of waffles would get broken during packaging, we definitely would have noticed. As our QC results are within spec, we believe that this will be related to some individual waffes (we assume that one or some indiviudal waffle was/were blocked in the oven, with a darker colour as result and some individual may have broken during packaging (but will not be widespread) or during transport. How many dark waffles has your customer found till now and how many broken waffles has your customer found till now? And shortage in cartons: do you mean bags were missing in cartons? Please inform me how many bags were missing and how many cartons. We have a carton weight checker and if bags are missing, the boxes must be rejected. My what's App number is 0032 473 5572 29
Subject: dark color, broken - item 308955 (P 12/02/2024)

TextBody: Hello Daniel Li, We have received your complaint and logged it in our system. I want to inform you that I have forwarded this complaint to our quality manager for further investigation. Although the customer describes it as hair, it am not 100% sure this is a human hair. I am waiting for the opinion of our quality department. But in case it would be human hair I can inform you that in all our production plants we have very stringent hygiene rules and measurements. All visitors, operators or working personnel have to wear hair nets and protective clothing. Also men with beards have to wear a beard net. We also have a procedure for how we have to put these on: first the hair and beard net have to be put on, afterwards the protective clothing, this is to avoid having hair on the protective clothing. Despite our best efforts, this can still occur exceptionally. I checked our quality records, but there were no issues reported that can explain this. We haven’t received other similar complaints on this batch. I will keep you informed as soon as I have heard more from our quality department.
Subject: FW: ATTENTION REQUIRED: Unknown Item Found Inside Maestro Hashbrown

TextBody: Dear Ciara, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00030679. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. There is a complete Quality Assurance system in place and the principles of HACCP are applied. This includes a full monitoring system on the production line. The finished products themselves are sampled every 60 minutes and examined for quality, including odeur and taste. Full records of these and all the other checks are maintained. Unfortunately we don't have a lotcode, so we cannot conduct a thorough investigation. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: 13573045 The Co-operative Quality Complaint - Hot Counter Hash Browns 600579

TextBody: Dear partners Yesterday, Wednesday, 6/12/2024, order No. 621 was received in Aqaba, which consists of 4 containers of Euro Gold S C 10*10 and two containers of Crinkle 12*12. When the containers were inspected by Jordanian customs employees in Aqaba, they found that the two containers sent from the Netherlands (the 12*12 crinkle) did not contain any evidence that they were made by the Netherlands in any way, unlike the goods sent from Belgium, which were marked on the Euro Gold potato 9*9. You can check the attached files to confirm. We tried to contact Mr. Martin and sent pictures to him via WhatsApp, but until now no one from you has contacted us to find out what is happening with us. Accordingly, customs in Aqaba decided to reserve the entire statement and required us to write a pledge not to sell until a report from the General Food and Drug Administration arrives to express its opinion on the matter. We ask you to follow up on the matter seriously and inform us of any information indicating that The crinkle 12*12 has any marking indicating that it was manufactured in the Netherlands. We will provide you with all the measures that will be taken by the Food and Drug Administration. B R SALIM AL WAHSH
Subject: P O NO 621

TextBody: Hello Hyunjin Based on the lotcode we were able to trace back the production date to 06/10/2023. Since we have the full lotcode available we could look to the exact time this product was packed : 21h43. This time is indeed not indicated in the results here below, but we can look at the hourly quality control checks which are performed most close to this time (21h03 and 22h05) There we see that the Agtron values are lower than average and therefore the wedges tend to be more dark. Hope to have informed you sufficiently.
Subject: Wedge claim in 60's chicken // FW: 유로골드 클레임 내용 공유 件

TextBody: Dear, Thank you for informing us about this case. Not all generic SKU's of Agristo have the origin on the bag/carton. I have looked into the history and I've seen that we have shipped this product already from 2022 without remarks. (the labels haven't changed) Any idea why the FDA are now looking into this? Can you please help me with the law instructions of Jordanië, so we can make sure we comply for the future shipments? In the meanwhile can we help with a statement for these containers, with declaration of origin and the explination that it concerns a human error? Our apologies if this has caused some inconvenience. Please help us understand what is required on the labels for Aqaba, so we can ship conform product.
Subject: P O NO 621

TextBody: Hello Daniel Li, I have received some more feedback from our quality department. Based on the photo, it is difficult to say if this is human hair, or a synthetic fiber (coming from textile for instance). But, they do not recognize it as something coming from our process/installation (like a cutting blade). Like explained below we have several measures in place to avoid human hair. Everyone in production has to wear special working clothes which are cleaned daily and quality of the clothes is inspected. Despite our best efforts, it is not possible to prevent this with 100% certainty. Of course our sincere apologies.
