TextBody: Hello Melissa, So sorry for the delay in answering your claim. We have well received your complaint and have registered it in our system as REF 00028877. We are very sorry to learn that you had a complaint about open sealing. Based on your lotcode, we have traced back the packaging day to 08/11/2023. Every hour the seals of the bags are tested. We checked the packaging and quality records of that day and no remarks were made. Both our quality and packaging personnel have not registered an anomaly. I also cannot relate the complaint to a reel change or any break downs. We suppose this is an isolated case. We hope that this letter has reassured you as to the precautions that we take with our products and to the good general quality of our products. We thank you for bringing this to our attention so that we may redouble our efforts. Please do not hesitate to contact me in case of further questions.
Subject: 600538 - Eden Farms Complaint on Farmer Jacks Crinkle Cut Chips 750g

TextBody: Hi David, Thank you for below e-mail. We are sorry to hear that the customer was not completely satisfied with the product. This complaint has been registered as case n° 00031488. I have inspected the quality records for the overall production, and then more specifically for these hours of production. We admit that this production did not get one of the best quality scores. Part of this production has been blocked, as too many critical defects were present, at this point, the veryx machines (optical sorters) were finetuned and set with narrower margins. This improved the number of defects and the product was again within the limits of the specifications. The batches received by this customer are from these approved batches. Do note that we work with a natural product, and variations in quality, especially towards the end of the season, are normal. We do set our machines as good as we can to catch these variations.
Subject: Quality claim 301143-MAO BNA

TextBody: Dear Hagino, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under case number 30351. We are sorry to hear that Toyota's customer was not satisfied with the quality of the Grand Farm natural cut potatoes. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Based on the provided pictures I have received, I can confirm this is a piece of sprout on the potato. Sprout can occur while the potatoes are being stored. Potatoes with sprout are still good for consumption, but the sprout should be removed. I have sent you a document with detailed information and explantion about sprout some months ago, after Toyota's visit. You can find it again enclosed. Sprout is normally removed by the hedgehog conveyor in potato reception, or by our optical sorters It appears that, despite our best efforts, some foreign material may have escaped our monitoring systems. Unfortunately, the batch code is not available, so I cannot conduct an investigation in the production records and quality documents for the batch in question. We are confident, however, that this complaint will not widespread. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact me again.
Subject: TOYOTA COMPLAINT FOR DISCOLORATIO AND SPROUTING ON NATURAL CUT

TextBody: Hi Michelle, Please find in annex the requested documents. Below the first investigation. Key points– if included in full investigation report; add comment ‘included in report’ Supplier Comments How many packs were produced? 5880 CAR (49 pallets) Line number Packagingline 13 (boxes) part A Productionline 6: gratin Date of production Packaging batch 1302126831 from 13/02/24-14/02/24 Related to production batch 1301033988 from 13/02/24 Were any issues or non-conformances recorded for this production; including foreign body controls and monitoring equipment? No product blocked on packaging order. No product blocked on production order. No notifications of Quality incidents on this packaging/production line on 13/02-14/02 (foreign bodies, glass incidents, metal incidents…) No irrigularities during Q-checks. Please outline the controls in place to prevent foreign material entering products -Approved suppliers of raw materials -Closed system for mixing potato slices and sauce -Manual packaging (= extra visual inspection) -Glass/plastic control measures. see annex. Have you reviewed retained samples / taste panel records - any deviation to specification? No, based on the photo, this does not come from our site. Item is intact so no reason to think that this is widespread. Are complaints recorded and monitored for Trending purposes? Yes, KPI-OPEX How are complaints communicated to Staff / Senior Team? Various ways: KPI meetings, TV screens, chef meetings… Could the root cause be identified? No Outline Corrective Actions No corrective actions: the piece does not match anything in our site. Based on the picture of the costumer we believe its a piece of like a coffee mug, where you have to push the lip away. We do not have this in our factory. We're hoping we can receive the piece of plastic from the costumer.
Subject: Iceland Customer Product Complaint 03369820

TextBody: Dear Hagino, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under case number 31432. We are sorry to hear that Toyota's customer was not satisfied with the quality of the Grand Farm shoestring fries. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Actually I can reconfirm what I have just sent you for the natural cut potatoes: Based on the provided pictures I have received, I can confirm this is a piece of sprout on the potato. Sprout can occur while the potatoes are being stored. Potatoes with sprout are still good for consumption, but the sprout should be removed. I have sent you a document with detailed information and explantion about sprout some months ago, after Toyota's visit. You can find it again enclosed. Sprout is normally removed by the hedgehog conveyor in potato reception, or by our optical sorters It appears that, despite our best efforts, some foreign material may have escaped our monitoring systems. Based on the batch codes I have received, I have done an investigation in the production records and quality documents for the batches in question. I can confirm that no remarks were noted on the production sheets. The production was thus done according to normal procedure. Moreover, no remarks about sprout were made during the hourly quality controls. We are therfore confident that this complaint will not be widespread. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact me again.
Subject: TOYOTA COMPLAINT FOR SHOESTRING WITH SPROUT

TextBody: Hi Ciara, Our quality department has received the FB and tested it. The particle was not recognised as coming from our factory. If the particle was really in the hashbrown, it must have already entered it at the beginning of our process from potato reception to moulding machine. here are several steps present to avoid foreign bodies. Possibly it came from the field and got into the product despite all our efforts? The process on this production line is fully automated with minimal manual handling. Since we have no lotcode, it is difficult to trace if there were non - conformities during the period of production.
Subject: 2491214 Tesco FB Complaint - Hash Browns 750g 600404

TextBody: Hello Françoise, We received a complaint from the client Rio Branco, reporting a sealing problem on 51 packages of 400g and 1,05kg . Here's their comments: "We have received complaints from Ticket customers (120267,120217,120360,120597,120422,120535), reporting faulty sealing on the 1.05kg and 400g potato packages. Report follows: 120267 Customer Hilton contacted us to complain that he bought 2 boxes of PIFPAF PALITO POTATO 1,05KG 10,5KG - AG and when he opened one of the boxes, 8 units of the potato were poorly sealed. 120217 Customer Mrs. Simone, contacted us complaining about the product PIFPAF PALITO POTATO 1,05KG 10,5KG - AG because the packaging was poorly sealed. The customer noticed the problem when he went to open the box and display it on the sales floor, noting that the bottom packages were opening at the top of the package. 120360 Customer contacted us to complain that he bought a box of PIFPAF PALITO POTATOES 1,05KG 10,5KG - AG and the packages came all open, poorly sealed. There was no sign of tampering on the box, everything was normal. Only the bags were open. The customer weighed the box and the weight was normal. 120422 Customer Mr. Eder, contacted us complaining about the product BATATA PALITO PIFPAF 400G 10KG - AG because there were 3 poorly sealed packages. The customer noticed the problem when he opened the box to put it on the sales floor. 120535 RCA Elisson contacted us on behalf of the customer, complaining about the product PIFPAF PALITO POTATO 400G 10KG - AG because it is poorly sealed on the back of the package. The customer noticed the problem when he went to replace the goods. 120597 Customer contacted us to complain that 5 packs of PIFPAF PALITO POTATOES 1,05KG 10,5KG - AG were open in the box. The problem was verified as soon as the customer opened the box. We request an immediate investigation into the causes of the non-conformity and the corrective actions that will be taken." TextBody: Dear Hagino, I have well received the claim below about a staple that was found inside a bag of Grand Farm shoestring fries. Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. I have promptly registered it in our system under case number 30356. We are veru sorry to hear that this situotion occured and that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this product. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : A0323 298 03:23 Packaging day : 2023.10.25 To eliminate the presence of metal, there is a metal detector installed on each packaging line. This in-line metal detector is positioned after the product is packed. When metal is detected, the product is automatically rejected and falls into a closed container. The detection of metal is carefully recorded and analyzed. We investigate the cause and origin of potential contamination and take the necessary corrective actions. The functioning of these metal detectors is tested every hour using test bars with sizes Ø2mm Fe, Ø 2mm Non Fe and Ø 3.5mm Stainless steel. We have a detailed metal detection procedure in place, and our packaging operators undergo annual training. A bag is taken out of a box after passing through the metal detector to insure there is no metal inside. The Ø 2mm Fe test bar is attached with tape to the bag and placed on the conveyor before the metal detector. When the bag is detected, this is repeated for Non Fe and Stainless steel. If the bag is not rejected, the packaging line is stopped and the packed products are blocked until the last positive control. These blocked bags are then rechecked using a properly functioning metal detector. Based on the batch code, I have conducted an investigation into our production records and quality documents for this particular batch. Enclosed you can find the results. As you can see, we can confirm the metal detector on the packing line in question (A03) was working correctly. I have highlighted the results of the tests that were done right before the bag in question was packed in green. I will ask our quality department to do a test on the packing line in question to see if the metal detector is able to detect a staple when it is inside a bag. I will come back to you with the results of the tests promptly. Please note that, if the staple would have come into our factory with the potatoes, it seems to be impossible that it would be able to go through the entire production flow without being rejected / detected. It would fall through the holes of the graders (of the potatoes and of the fries) for example. I will also get back to you with the answer to your other questions soon. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered.
Subject: TOYOTA COMPLAINT FOR A STAPLE IN BAG OF SHOESTRINGS

TextBody: Bonjour Alexis, Veuillez trouver ci-dessous l'analyse de notre service de qualité/packaging: Dans vos plaintes, il s'agit principalement de 2 codes de lot: D03 24 107 - D05 24 12. En analysant les codes horaires que nous avons reçus jusqu'à présent pour ces codes de lot (pour D03 24 107: 5h45 - 6h44 - 6h57 et pour D05 24 121: 21h40 - 21h38), ils semblent tous assez proches les uns des autres (dans 1 jour de production). A première vue, on constate alors que pas tout le cycle de production a été affecté. Ils ont ensuite vérifié les échantillons de rétention internes des deux code de lot. Ci-dessous vous trouvez les détails des échantillons et les codes de lot correspondants. Batch Code de lot 1302130864 D03241070321 1302130864 D03241070501 1302130864 D03241071312 1302132763 D05241210613 1302132763 D05241211307 1302132763 D05241212103 1302132763 D05241220503 Aucun des échantillons ne présentait de soudure ouverte. Cela confirme donc nos soupçons que le problème n'est pas généralisé pour tout le cycle de production. Nous comprenons la gravité des plaintes, mais nous espérons qu’avec les informations ci-dessus, nous vous avons rassuré de ne pas faire de retraite. Quant à la cause, on n'a pas encore eu des nouvelles de notre service de packaging. Evidemment, je vous tiens au courant si j'ai des nouvelles. TextBody: Dear Sir or Madam, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. I have promptly registered it in our system under case number 30979. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of the EDEKA Dicke Fritte. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Batch code: G24 24 120 05:42 Production day: 29/04/2024 After reviewing the picture/description, it appears that indeed, this is some product / batter crum. It is likely that some build-up of product/batter (coating) has occurred on a part of the production equipment. This must then have become dislodged during the production. Normally this kind of crum is removed by the optical sorter after freezing. It appears that, despite our best efforts, some foreign material may have escaped our monitoring system Based on the batch code, I have conducted an investigation into our production records and quality documents for this specific batch. I can confirm that our records do not show any anomaly during production or any remarks in this regard on the QC documents. Therefore, we are confident that this complaint is not widespread. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered. If you have any further concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us again.
Subject: Referenz #GeVo2003604126: Issue: 2003596106, [ Beschwerde ] EDEKA, EDEKA Dicke Fritte 750g, Agristo NV27.4.26, G24 24120 05:42

Therefore we made 2 ticketreferences in our internal quality system ticket 31599 (referring to packaging date 22/03/2024) and ticket (reffering to packaging date 04/03/2024). TextBody: Dear Aswin, we have investigated this case, and can confirm you with certainty that this foreign object cannot have ended up in our product. The flakes line has an optical sorter at intake, which is equipeed with cameras. Depending on the settings and the detected defect, the unwanted materials/potatoes are removed from the product stream using mechanical valves. The valves then remove the materials/potatoes to exit 1, which is 'foreign objects'. In the entire production process, 7 sieves are installed, through which large objects such as the one in your picture, cannot end up in the flakes (maximum allowed size is 5mm). packing of the flakes is a closed process in which foreign objects from outside of our plant cannot end up. we checked with our technical service, who keep lists of all elements used in our machine park and in the factory, and, based on this picture, we can confirm that this yellow plastic/polyester-like object is not used in our factory. I hope this information reassures you that this foreign object is not coming from our factory.
Subject: Customer complaint- Foreign body

Bonjour, Nous avons bien reçu votre notification ci-dessous, qui a été enregistrée sous la reference 30908 Sur la bas du code lot, nous confirmerons que les frites ont été produits le 15 décembre 2023. * Lot: G 23 349 14h50 * Batch: 1033424 * Date: 15/12/2023 Tout d’abord, je voudrais vous informer que nous avons un système d’assurance qualité en place, dans lequel le produit final est soumis à un contrôle approfondi toutes les heures. Lors de ces contrôles, le nombre de défauts est également mesuré. Pour m’assurer que nous nous comrenons, j'aimerais savoir comment vous enregistrez les défauts ? Dans nos contrôles, les défauts sont comptés par nombre/1000g. Les valeurs dont vous parlez s'écartent également légèrement de nos valeurs prédéterminées. Veuillez voir nos commentaires dans le document ci-joint. En examinant les contrôles en détail, nous constatons qu'ils sont conformes à la spécification, mais qu'ils tendent parfois vers la limite. À titre d'action, nous avons déjà extrait des échantillons de rétention du code de lot en question à des fins de vérification. Comme vous pouvez le voir sur la photo ci-jointe, ils ne présentent pas de défauts excessifs. Bien entendu, nous nous efforçons toujours d'éliminer le plus de défauts possible de notre processus de production et d'ajuster les trieurs optiques avec précision. Cependant, nous travaillons avec un produit naturel, et nous nous efforçons toujours d'obtenir la meilleure qualité possible. Nous espérons pouvoir vous aider et restons à votre disposition pour toute question supplémentaire. TextBody: Hello Patricia Thank you for raising the issue here below regarding the non conformity of the nutritional table printed on the packaging. Based on the clear image you were able to provide us, we were able to perform an investigation regarding this matter. Product : Gelcampo Batata Pré-frita Pal. 10x10 mm 2 kg Lot: L C05 24 111 01:31 Production date: 20/04/2021 Every hour different quality checks are performed by the operator on the packaging line. The check of the printing quality of the bag stamp is also included in these quality checks. All of these checks are registered. I have consulted the corresponding packaging and quality records of that day and no remarks were made. Both our quality and packaging workers have not registered any anomaly. I therefore can assure you that this concerns an isolated case and this is not spread over the other stock to be loaded next week. Please understand that the nutritional information is printed to the packaging by inkjet. This printing quality is less sharp than the preprinted information on the packaging. To avoid similar remarks in the future I have made the table lines of the nutritional table thicker. As per your last request we removed importer 'Gelcampo' and replaced it by 'Super Rede'. Can you confirm if this information can be printed during the next production run? Without mistake I didn't receive your approval on this latest amend? Hope to have informed you sufficiently. If you have any other doubts do not hesitate to reach out.
Subject: RE: Setup Gelcampo brand - Labels NOK

TextBody: Dear Ana Žaja, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00031552. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : G022411711 Packaging day : 26/04/2024 I would like to reassure you that during the packing process, we conduct quality checks. Our team tests the seals of the bags on an hourly basis. A box is removed from the packaging line, and all bags are meticulously inspected to ensure that the seals are properly closed. These inspection results are recorded in our Quality documents. In light of the concerns you raised, we have conducted an investigation into the packaging checks for the particular batch. You will receive an electronic credit note shortly. We regret any inconvenience this issue may have caused you or your customer. We take this matter seriously and are committed to preventing such incidents in the future. Should you require any further information or assistance, please do not hesitate to contact us.

TextBody: EDEKA Kunden- und Ernährungsservice GUT&GÜNSTIG Backofenfrites Finschnitt 1000g Issue Number: 2003612484 URGENT! Dear sir or madam, we received the following customer’s complaint through our customer service. We expect you to review the incident immediately and send a first detailed statement within two hours after receiving this mail. Please see below for the reason for complaint and product details. Product: Article: Backofenfrites Finschnitt 1000g Brand: GUT&GÜNSTIG BBD: 4.2026 Lot: A02 24 113 12:49 Issue: Good day "See attached photos. According to the customer, the wire in the small bag was in the bag of chips. I have photographed the batch number. I also have the wire and bag here on site. The customer has not suffered any damage, but will ask again next week again next week to find out how this could have happened." _________ Guten Tag „siehe Fotos Anhang. Der Draht in der kleinen Tüte befand sich laut Kunde in der Pommestüte. Chargennummer hab ich fotografiert. Draht und Tüte habe ich auch hier vor Ort. Der Kunde hat keinen Schaden erlitten, fragt aber nächste Woche nochmal nach, ob es Erkenntnisse gibt, wie das passieren konnte.“ ________________________________ We expect a detailed and comprehensive statement regarding this complaint. Please carry out a thorough investigation and provide us the result of the investigation within the a.m. timeframe. Please include answers to the following questions as well: 1. When was the production of the product? 2. Did you notice any entry of metallic foreign bodies in the relevant production period? 3. Have you received any further complaints? 4. What preventive measures against the entry of metallic foreign bodies exist in the production facility? 5. Are metal detectors used in your production facility? At what point(s) are they installed (detailed description including photos required)? What sensitivity do the detectors have for different types of metal? By whom are checks of the metal detectors carried out and how often is it done? What do you use as reference for a successful detection test? How and at which point on the line are the products discharged in the event of a successful detection? Are there any technical devices that indicate a failure of the detector or of the discharge? Who has access to the metal detectors and the black box? 6. Do you know the exact compositions of all metal objects used in the production plant? 7. Are all metal items in your production facility detectable by X-ray or metal detectors? 8. To what extent is there a possibility of the introduction of metallic foreign bodies through raw materials or packaging materials? 9. Are the production lines completely covered? 10. Are all employees trained regarding the risk of foreign bodies? 11. Are there any contract workers employed in your production facility? 12. Were there any service workers or engineers working during production? Please send us an excerpt of your HACCP concept regarding metal and foreign body and your current IFS-certificate. Please let us know what quantities of the relevant production lot have been shipped and to which warehouses. When were the goods delivered? Were any further goods delivered after this particular batch/lot (when, and in what quantities)? Please send your statement solely by email, maintaining the original subject to reklamation@edeka.de<mailto:reklamation@edeka.de> and the whole mailing list of this email. If you are missing any product details, please let us know. Nevertheless we ask you to answer all questions where possible. Please send us the missing details once you received the missing product details. Thanks! Should you have further documents or information available that might help resolving the complaint, please add these as well. Should you require any further information, please do not hesitate to contact us.

TextBody: Dear Sir or Madam, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. I have promptly registered it in our system under case number 31755. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Batch code: A02 24 113 12:49 Packing day: 22/04/2024 Besides the steps that are already taken during the production process (optical sorters for example), to eliminate the presence of metal foreign bodies, there is a metal detector installed on each packaging line. This in-line metal detector is positioned after the product is packed. When metal is detected, the product is automatically rejected and falls into a closed container. The detection of metal is carefully recorded and analyzed. We investigate the cause and origin of potential contamination and take the necessary corrective actions. The functioning of these metal detectors is tested every hour using test bars with sizes Ø2mm Fe, Ø 2mm Non Fe and Ø 3.5mm Stainless steel. We have a detailed metal detection procedure in place, and our packing line operators undergo annual training. A bag is taken out of a box after passing through the metal detector to insure there is no metal inside. The Ø 2mm Fe test bar is attached with tape to the bag and placed on the conveyor before the metal detector. When the bag is detected, this is repeated for Non Fe and Stainless steel. If the bag is not rejected, the packaging line is stopped and the packed products are blocked until the last positive control. These blocked bags are then rechecked using a properly functioning metal detector. Based on the batch code, I have conducted an investigation into our production records and quality documents for this particular batch. As you can see on the results enclosed, I can confirm that the metal detector on the packing line in question (A02) was working correctly at the time the product was packed (test that were done before and after the product was packed are highlighted in green). Could you please send the metal piece to the address provided below for further examination? This will allow us to determine if the metal was rejected during the online inspection and if anyone can recognize the piece. Agristo nv For the attention of Jeroen Perseyn Waterstraat 40 8531 Harelbeke Belgium with reference to our case number 31755 I added the answer to your questions in blue in your e-mail below and added the requested documents enclosed. If you need any further information, please do not hesitate to contact me. We apologize for any inconvenience that you may have suffered.
Subject: Referenz #GeVo2003612677: PRIO-1 Complaint metal, Issue: 2003612484, [GUT&GÜNSTIG, 4.2026, A02 24 113 12:49]

TextBody: Dear Kathleen, I sent you a video which shows one carton has 9 bags (1 bag shortage). I am waiting for JY to provide more information and the total affected quantity. Jack Lo From: Agristo Claims <claims@agristo.com> Sent: Thursday, June 13, 2024 8:06 PM To: taiwanfood@seed.net.tw Cc: beau.declerck@agristo.com Subject: RE: dark color, broken - item 308955 (P 12/02/2024) Dear Jack Lo, We are very sorry to hear you have reason to complaint. Based on the given lot code D05 24 043 1643, I could trace back production date and I could check our quality and production records. According to our QC log files and production files, there were no issues reported. The colour was within spec and we did not struggle with broken product. We check the product after it has been packed in bags. If a lot of waffles would get broken during packaging, we definitely would have noticed. As our QC results are within spec, we believe that this will be related to some individual waffes (we assume that one or some indiviudal waffle was/were blocked in the oven, with a darker colour as result and some individual may have broken during packaging (but will not be widespread) or during transport. How many dark waffles has your customer found till now and how many broken waffles has your customer found till now? And shortage in cartons: do you mean bags were missing in cartons? Please inform me how many bags were missing and how many cartons. We have a carton weight checker and if bags are missing, the boxes must be rejected. My what's App number is 0032 473 5572 29
Subject: dark color, broken - item 308955 (P 12/02/2024)

TextBody: Hello Rachel, We have received your complaint and are sorry for this inconvenience. Lot code: A04240390901 Production date: 08/02/2024 We have investigated this code from both our process sheets and the library samples, tasting sheets and daily management panel. We can confirm that the fried colour was showing some variation between darker chips and also lighter chips, but all within spec. We allow a colour variation between Agtron 60-70 and at 09h the Agtron was 60, so at the darker site of the range, but still acceptable. According to the photo's of you customer, we see fries with sugar points or glassy potatoes. Sugar points occur more at the end of the season when starch converts to sugars in the potato as it is stored for longer. We have very detailed checks for the sugars on potato intake and during production. But even within the potatoes from one delivery, from part of a field, the sugars can vary and not be detected. We adjust our blanchers based on the intake records to reduce the sugars and colour. If it is extreme we reject a full load of raw potatoes. Our QC records show that we did not struggle with sugar points or glassy potatoes. We know for sure from our regular checks throughout the run that this was a good run. This makes us believe that only a small pocket of potatoes will be affected by a higher level of sugars. We hope that this letter has reassured you as to the precautions that we take with our products and to the good general quality of our products. We thank you for bringing this to our attention. Please do not hesitate to contact me in case of further questions.
Subject: FW: Feedback - Fries colour

TextBody: Bonjour, Je tenais à vous informer de l'évolution de cette plainte. Nous avons fait une investigation avec notre department de qualité. Basé sur l'investigation, le produit a été emballé et produit le 11/03/2024. Basé sur les photos, il semble que les corps étrangers ne semblent pas être passés par une friteuse, de sorte que les chances qu'ils soient arrivés avec eux depuis le champ et qu'ils aient traversé l'ensemble du flux de production sont pratiquement inexistantes. Pour nos clients en vrac, nous préparons et remplissons nos cartons en interne. Normalement, un sac bleu est toujours inséré, rempli et fermé. Le bois n'est peut-être pas détecté, mais il est interdit dans la production. Sur la base des informations contenues dans votre document supplémentaire, nous avons appris que les corps étrangers se trouvaient entre la palette et le vrac et non dans le produit. Cela aurait pu se produire pendant le transport ou à la réception. Bien à vous, Françoise Françoise De Vrieze Technical Sales Officer P +32 56 54 10 63 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Agristo Claims [claims@agristo.com] Sent: 14/06/2024 10:02 To: marine.catherin@mousquetaires.com Cc: francois.trannoy@mousquetaires.com; melanie.jeuland-vallee@mousquetaires.com Subject: RE: Réclamation AC 519/2024 Bonjour madame Catherin, Nous avons bien recu cette plainte concernant les corps étranger. Nous l'avons enrégistré dans notre système d'assurance de qualité comme réference 31577. Nous sommes désollées que vous avez eu ce problème. Nous allons examiner cette question avec notre service qualité et notre service d'emballage. Je vous tiendrai au courant de l'évolution de la situation. Je vous remercie pour votre patience. Bien à vous, Françoise Françoise De Vrieze Technical Sales Officer P +32 56 54 10 63 --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Marine CATHERIN [marine.catherin@mousquetaires.com] Sent: 13/06/2024 17:16 To: claims@agristo.com Cc: francois.trannoy@mousquetaires.com; melanie.jeuland-vallee@mousquetaires.com Subject: Réclamation AC 519/2024 Bonjour, Veuillez trouver ci-joint une fiche de réclamation fournisseur ainsi que la photo correspondante. Graag hadden wij een eerste reactie uiterlijk binnen de 48u ontvangen na ontvangst van deze klacht. TextBody: Hi, As the FB was not detected and rejected by the optical sorter originally this suggests the complaint is justified. Due to the nature of the complaint we need to establish the root cause and corrective actions. Please could you respond to the below: * Why was the FB not rejected by the optical sorter originally? Could you provide some detail on the parameter changes that resulted in the FB being detected? * Your response previously mentioned sorting checks not related to the optical sorter. Could you elaborate on these checks? * Has this complaint been communicated with relevant personnel? * Have the operators carrying out the sorting checks been retrained?
Subject: SERIOUS 2503002 Tesco FB Complaint - Spicy Potato Wedges 750g 600413

TextBody: Dear, Thank you for bringing this matter to our attention. We have promptly registered it in our system under ticket number 00031593. We are sorry to hear that your customer was not satisfied with the quality of this batch. The quality of our products is of utmost importance to us and we are committed to resolving this matter. Batch information: Lotcode : C04233390538 Packaging day : 5/12/2023 I would like to reassure you that during the packing process, we conduct quality checks. Our team tests the seals of the bags on an hourly basis. A box is removed from the packaging line, and all bags are meticulously inspected to ensure that the seals are properly closed. These inspection results are recorded in our Quality documents. In light of the concerns you raised, we have conducted an investigation into the packaging checks for the particular batch. No remarks were made. We regret any inconvenience this issue may have caused you or your customer. We take this matter seriously and are committed to preventing such incidents in the future. Should you require any further information or assistance, please do not hesitate to contact us.
Subject: BRF Claim - Protocolo 2950973
